===童年，流离，青少年===
吉布森出生于[[美国|美国]][[南卡罗来纳州|南卡罗来纳州]]临海城市[[康威_(南卡罗来纳州)|康威]]，童年大部分时间在父母生长的故乡，[[阿巴拉契亚山脉|阿巴拉契亚山脉]]中的小镇[[弗吉尼亚州|弗吉尼亚州]][[威斯维尔_(弗吉尼亚州)|威斯维尔]]度过。<ref name="sourcecode"/><ref name="observer">{{cite news |url=http://books.guardian.co.uk/departments/sciencefiction/story/0,,2146989,00.html |title=Space to think |access-date=2007-10-26 |last=Adams |first=Tim |author2=Emily Stokes |author3=James Flint |date=2007-08-12 |work=The Observer |location=London |archive-date=2007-10-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071016221155/http://books.guardian.co.uk/departments/sciencefiction/story/0,,2146989,00.html |url-status=no }}</ref>吉布森小时候，家里因为他父亲在大型建筑企业的管理工作经常搬家。<ref name="litencyc">{{cite web | last =Rapatzikou | first =Tatiani | title =William Gibson | website =[[The_Literary_Encyclopedia|The Literary Encyclopedia]] | publisher =The Literary Dictionary Company | date =2003-06-17 | url =http://www.litencyc.com/php/speople.php?rec=true&UID=5198 | access-date =2007-08-27 | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20071010051539/http://www.litencyc.com/php/speople.php?rec=true&UID=5198 | archive-date =2007-10-10 | url-status =yes }}</ref>吉布森在弗吉尼亚州[[诺福克_(弗吉尼亚州)|诺福克]]就读派恩斯小学（Pines Elementary School）。学校老师不鼓励吉布森读书，他父母对此感到不悦。<ref name=sale>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/passedfailed-william-gibson-novelist-and-scriptwriter-541221.html|title=Passed/Failed: William Gibson, novelist and scriptwriter|work=[[The_Independent|The Independent]]|access-date=2009-03-12|date=2003-06-19|last=Sale|first=Jonathan|publisher=[[Independent_News_&_Media|Independent News & Media]]|location=London}}{{Dead link}}</ref>吉布森年幼时，{{efn|1={{Tsl|en|New York Times Magazine|纽约时报杂志}}<ref name="nytmag1"/>和吉布森本人<ref name="sourcecode"/>称他父亲死时自己六岁，而研究吉布森的学者塔蒂亚妮·拉帕齐库（Tatiani Rapatzikou） 在 《{{Tsl|en|The Literary Encyclopedia|文学百科全书}}》中称他丧父时八岁。<ref name="litencyc"/>}}上小学一年多，<ref name=sale/>父亲出差时在餐馆噎死。<ref name="sourcecode"/>母亲无法把这一噩耗告诉吉布森，让他人转达了他父亲的死讯。<ref name="nytmag1">{{cite news| last = Solomon| first = Deborah| title = Questions for William Gibson: Back From the Future| page = 13| work = [[The_New_York_Times_Magazine|The New York Times Magazine]]| date = 2007-08-19| url = https://www.nytimes.com/2007/08/19/magazine/19wwln-q4-t.html?partner=rssnyt&emc=rss| access-date = 2007-10-13| archive-date = 2013-05-12| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130512113209/http://www.nytimes.com/2007/08/19/magazine/19wwln-q4-t.html?partner=rssnyt&emc=rss| url-status = no}}</ref>{{Tsl|en|Tom Maddox|汤姆·迈达克斯}}评论道：吉布森“生长在一个和[[J·G·巴拉德|J·G·巴拉德]]的梦境一样令人不安的、光怪陆离的美国”。<ref name="Virus 23">{{cite web|url=http://www.dthomasmaddox.com/virus23.html|title=Maddox on Gibson|access-date=2007-10-26|last=Maddox|first=Tom|author-link=Tom Maddox|year=1989|quote=This story originally appeared in a Canadian 'zine, Virus '''23''', 1989.|url-status=yes|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071013205424/http://dthomasmaddox.com/virus23.html|archive-date=2007-10-13}}</ref>
{{Quote box|align=left|width=40%|失去能给艺术家带来一些奇特的长处。我尊敬的艺术家不少都经历过痛心的生离死别。|salign=right|source=——2007年8月19日威廉·吉布森在{{Tsl|en|New York Times Magazine|纽约时报杂志}}上的采访<ref name="nytmag1"/>}}
父亲去世几天后，吉布森和母亲搬回了威斯维尔。<ref name="observer"/><ref name="nomaps"/>吉布森后来把威斯维尔形容为“一个[[现代性|现代性]]虽然算是来到，但深受怀疑的地方”，并认为他与科幻文学的联系，他的“原生文学文化”，就是从忽然被放逐的感受中起源的。<ref name="nomaps"/><ref name="sourcecode">{{cite web|last =Gibson|first =William|date =2002-11-06|url =http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/source/source.asp|title =Since 1948|access-date =2007-11-04|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20071120193555/http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/source/source.asp|archive-date =2007-11-20|url-status =yes}}</ref>吉布森十二岁时，“一心只想当科幻小说家”。<ref name=newscientist>{{cite journal|journal=[[New_Scientist|New Scientist]]|access-date=2008-11-17|title=Sci-fi special: William Gibson|first=William|last=Gibson|date=2008-11-12|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg20026821.600-scifi-special-william-gibson.html|archive-date=2008-11-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081121072258/http://www.newscientist.com/article/mg20026821.600-scifi-special-william-gibson.html|url-status=no}}</ref>他就读热衷篮球的乔治·威斯高中（George Wythe High School），荒废了几年，大把时间待在自己房间里听唱片、读书。<ref name=sale/>十三岁那年，吉布森瞒着母亲买了一本[[垮掉的一代|垮掉的一代]]文选，从而接触到了[[艾伦·金斯堡|艾伦·金斯堡]]、[[杰克·凯鲁亚克|杰克·凯鲁亚克]]、[[威廉·巴勒斯|威廉·巴勒斯]]的作品；巴勒斯对吉布森的影响尤其深远，使他对科幻文学大为改观。<ref name="god's little toys">{{cite journal|url=https://www.wired.com/wired/archive/13.07/gibson.html|title=God's Little Toys: Confessions of a cut & paste artist|last=Gibson|first=William|date=July 2005|journal=[[Wired.com|Wired.com]]|access-date=2007-11-04|archive-date=2007-02-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070221101831/http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/13.07/gibson.html|url-status=no}}</ref><ref name="project cyberpunk interview">{{cite book | last = McCaffery | first = Larry | author-link = Larry McCaffery | title = Storming the Reality Studio: a casebook of cyberpunk and postmodern science fiction | access-date = 2007-11-05 | publisher = [[Duke_University_Press|Duke University Press]] | location = [[Durham,_North_Carolina|Durham, North Carolina]] | isbn = 978-0-8223-1168-3 | oclc = 23384573 | pages = 263–285 | chapter = An Interview with William Gibson | chapter-url = http://project.cyberpunk.ru/idb/gibson_interview.html | year = 1991 | title-link = science fiction | archive-date = 2012-01-25 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120125090151/http://project.cyberpunk.ru/idb/gibson_interview.html | url-status = no }}</ref>青少年时期的吉布森性格笨拙腼腆。他生长在他认为“大有问题”<ref name=newscientist/>的单一文化环境中，自觉地远离宗教，读科幻小说、巴勒斯和[[亨利·米勒|亨利·米勒]]的作品作为生活上的寄托。<ref name="nomaps"/><ref name="seattle pi">{{cite news |first=John |last=Marshall |title=William Gibson's new novel asks, is the truth stranger than science fiction today? |url=http://www.seattlepi.com/books/107368_gibson06.shtml |department=Books |work=[[Seattle_Post-Intelligencer|Seattle Post-Intelligencer]] |date=2003-02-06 |access-date=2007-11-03 |archive-date=2021-04-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210419035408/https://www.seattlepi.com/ae/books/article/William-Gibson-s-new-novel-asks-is-the-truth-1106809.php |url-status=no }}</ref>吉布森学习成绩不好，他母亲不满意，威胁他要把他送到寄宿制学校；结果他母亲惊讶地发现吉布森很乐意。<ref name=sale/>当时吉布森的母亲“长期焦虑，患有[[抑郁症|抑郁症]]”，自从丧夫之后就一直待在威斯维尔，付不起送吉布森去他想去的[[加州南部|加州南部]]的费用，把他送到了[[图森_(亚利桑那州)|图森]]的南亚利桑那州男子学校（Southern Arizona School for Boys）。<ref name="sourcecode"/><ref name="observer"/><ref name="nomaps"/>他愤恨私立寄宿制学校的管理结构，但后来回忆时，却感激这段生活逼迫他社交。<ref name=sale/>吉布森在[[SAT|SAT]]考试中，写作部分得了148分（满分150分），但数学部分只得了5分（满分150分），他的老师都不满意。<ref name=sale/>

===逃役，放逐，反文化===
[[File:Uncle_Gibby.jpg|thumb]]《{{Tsl|en|Spook Country|幽灵山村}}》读者见面会上的吉布森。自从1985年受《温哥华杂志》之托，写下要求以温哥华为背景的《{{Tsl|en|The Winter Market|冬季市场}}》之后，吉布森一直极力避免设定他客居的这座城市为他作品的背景，直到写下《幽灵山村》这部作品，才打破循规<ref name="vancouver">{{cite news |first=Joe |last=Wiebe |title=Writing Vancouver |url=http://www.canada.com/vancouversun/news/arts/story.html?id=99d2236b-c329-4969-b07e-6ffebeff5871 |work=[[The_Vancouver_Sun|The Vancouver Sun]] |date=2007-10-13 |access-date=2017-03-04 |url-status=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022231428/http://www.canada.com/vancouversun/news/arts/story.html?id=99d2236b-c329-4969-b07e-6ffebeff5871 |archive-date=2012-10-22 }}</ref>]]
吉布森年仅十八岁时，母亲就去世了。<ref name=sale/>吉布森从此离校，没有毕业，很长时间孑然一身，去了加州和欧洲旅行，融入到反文化之中。<ref name="observer"/><ref name="nomaps"/><ref name="seattle pi"/>1967年，他“{{Tsl|en|Draft dodger#Vietnam War|逃役|逃避因越南战争实行的兵役}}”，前往加拿大定居。<ref name=sourcecode/><ref name="nomaps"/>当时，在兵役[[聆讯|聆讯]]上，他对面试官坦白道，他人生的目的就是把每一种[[精神药物|精神药物]]都尝试一遍。<ref name="riding shotgun"/>吉布森评论他自己的行为，说他“不算真的逃了兵役，反正他们也没征我”；<ref name=sourcecode />聆讯结束后，他回家买了张去多伦多的公交车票，一两周后就上路了。<ref name="nomaps">{{cite AV media |people= [[Mark_Neale|Mark Neale]] (director), William Gibson (subject) |title=[[No_Maps_for_These_Territories|No Maps for These Territories]] |publisher=Docurama |medium=Documentary |date =2000}}</ref>在2000年拍摄的，给吉布森作传的纪录片《{{Tsl|en|No Maps for These Territories|威廉·吉布森的旅行}}》中，吉布森说他的动机与其说是[[良心拒服兵役者|良心拒服兵役]]，不如说更多的是想“跟嬉皮士小妞睡觉”和使劲抽[[大麻|大麻]]。<ref name="nomaps"/>他在2008年的一次采访中，就这个话题阐述了一番：
{{quote|我开始当作家的时候，标榜自己逃役，这不应该。我脑子里有点模糊的想法，想逃兵役，就来了加拿大，可我从来就没被征召，所以压根没必要做这个决定。我也不知道，如果真被征召，我会怎么办。我当时也没个主心骨。要是他们把我征了，我估计就哭一场，然后跟他们去了。当然，我肯定不会喜欢服役的。|source=2008年6月10日威廉·吉布森在{{Tsl|en|io9}}上的采访<ref>{{cite interview |last=Gibson |first=William |interviewer=[[Annalee_Newitz|Annalee Newitz]] |title=William Gibson Talks to io9 About Canada, Draft Dodging, and Godzilla |location=[[San_Francisco|San Francisco]] |date=June 10, 2008 |work=[[io9|io9]] |url=http://io9.com/5015137/william-gibson-talks-to-io9-about-canada-draft-dodging-and-godzilla |access-date=June 10, 2008 |archive-date=2008-06-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080611081540/http://io9.com/5015137/william-gibson-talks-to-io9-about-canada-draft-dodging-and-godzilla |url-status=no }}</ref>}}
“流浪”了几个星期之后，吉布森被多伦多首家{{Tsl|en|head shop}}（贩卖吸毒用具的商店）聘为管理员。<ref name=desertisland>{{cite episode |title=William Gibson |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio4/features/desert-island-discs/castaway/3ade8915#p00941v7 |access-date=June 27, 2011 |series=Desert Island Discs |series-link=Desert Island Discs |network=BBC |station=[[BBC_Radio_4|BBC Radio 4]] |airdate=November 19, 1999 |time=16:41 |quote=有那么几个星期实际上我算是流浪了，但那是一段愉快宜人，飘忽不定的时光，现在想起那时候是在流浪我都觉得很奇怪。后来慢慢地，呃，不如说我很快就成了多伦多第一家head shop的管理员。 |archive-date=2011-04-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110430113632/http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio4/features/desert-island-discs/castaway/3ade8915#p00941v7 |url-status=no }}</ref>吉布森发现自己无法忍受深陷于抑郁症、自杀和硬毒品之中的美国逃役流亡者群体。<ref name="nomaps"/>1967年[[爱之夏|爱之夏]]，他在[[加拿大广播公司|加拿大广播公司]]介绍[[多伦多|多伦多]][[約威老|約威老]]嬉皮士[[次文化|次文化]]的新闻片中出镜，<ref>{{cite AV media |url= http://www.cbc.ca/archives/entry/yorkville-hippie-haven |title= Yorkville: Hippie haven |date= 1967-09-04 |format= 14 min [[Windows_Media_Video|Windows Media Video]]; "This is Bill" appears first after 0:45 |access-date= 2021-05-24 |archive-date= 2020-11-12 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201112022931/https://www.cbc.ca/archives/entry/yorkville-hippie-haven/ |dead-url= no }} {{cite AV media |url= http://archives.cbc.ca/IDC-1-69-1587-10799/life_society/60s/clip11 |title= Rochdale College: Organized anarchy |format= 16 min radio recording [[Windows_Media_Audio|Windows Media Audio]]; interviews start after 4:11 |publisher= [[CBC.ca|CBC.ca]] |location= [[Yorkville,_Toronto|Yorkville, Toronto]] |access-date= 2008-02-01 |archive-date= 2008-01-15 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20080115180348/http://archives.cbc.ca/IDC-1-69-1587-10799/life_society/60s/clip11 |dead-url= no }}</ref>片酬“五百元”，相当于二十个星期的租金，被他充作旅费。<ref name="cbc yorkville">{{cite web |url=http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_05_01_archive.asp#200226493 |title=That CBC Archival Footage |access-date=2007-11-26 |last=Gibson |first=William |date=2003-05-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071210172818/http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_05_01_archive.asp#200226493 |archive-date=2007-12-10 |url-status=yes }}</ref>除了在[[华盛顿特区|华盛顿特区]]待过“被骚乱撕裂的短短一阵”之外，吉布森在1960年代后几年都待在多伦多；这段时间他邂逅了温哥华人黛博拉·简·汤普森<ref name="deb">{{cite news |url= https://www.theguardian.com/books/2003/may/03/sciencefictionfantasyandhorror.williamgibson |title= Profile: William Gibson |first= Steven |last= Poole |date= 2003-05-03 |access-date= 2010-04-27 |work= guardian.co.uk |location= London |archive-date= 2014-01-25 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140125042144/http://www.theguardian.com/books/2003/may/03/sciencefictionfantasyandhorror.williamgibson |url-status= no }}</ref>，后来和她一起去了欧洲旅行。<ref name=sourcecode/>吉布森回忆到，他们专门去法西斯当政、汇率划算的欧洲国家，包括1970年在希腊的某群岛上以及[[伊斯坦布尔|伊斯坦布尔]]待过一段时间，<ref name="obsession"/>因为他们“但凡是用的钱有一点儿像硬通货的地方都去不起”。<ref name="rogers">{{cite web |url=http://w2.eff.org/Misc/Publications/William_Gibson/rogers_gibson.interview |title=In Same Universe |access-date=2007-11-06 |first=Mike |last=Rogers |date=1993-10-01 |publisher=Lysator Sweden Science Fiction Archive |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070419180411/http://www.georgetown.edu/faculty/irvinem/english016/gibson/gibson2.int |archive-date=2007-04-19 |dead-url=no }}</ref>1972年，两人结婚，定居在温哥华，吉布森照看他们的第一个孩子，一家人靠他妻子当教师的薪水生活。1970年代，吉布森很大程度上靠在[[救世军|救世军]]旧货店里搜罗低价工艺品，再高价卖给专门经销商过活。<ref name="obsession">{{cite journal |url=https://www.wired.com/wired/archive/7.01/ebay.html |title=My Obsession |last=Gibson |first=William |access-date=2007-12-02 |journal=[[Wired_(magazine)|Wired.com]] |volume=7 |date=January 1999 |issue=1 |archive-date=2008-05-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080513141906/http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/7.01/ebay.html |url-status=no }}</ref>他发觉在大学保持好成绩可以拿不菲的奖学金，这比工作挣钱容易得多，<ref name="project cyberpunk interview"/>便就读了[[不列颠哥伦比亚大学|不列颠哥伦比亚大学]]，在1977年取得了“一个没什么用的英语学士学位”。<ref name="sourcecode"/><ref>{{cite journal|date        = 2004-03-04|title        = UBC Alumni: The First Cyberpunk|journal        = UBC Reports|volume        = 50|issue        = 3|url        = http://www.publicaffairs.ubc.ca/ubcreports/2004/04mar04/gibson.html|access-date        = 2007-11-02|archive-url        = https://web.archive.org/web/20080108011400/http://www.publicaffairs.ubc.ca/ubcreports/2004/04mar04/gibson.html|archive-date        = 2008-01-08|url-status        = yes}}</ref>研习[[英语文学|英语文学]]使吉布森接触了大量他原本不会读的虚构文学作品，他认为这些作品给他提供了科幻文化中接触不到的想法，包括对[[后现代主义|后现代主义]]的意识。<ref name="crier"/>吉布森在不列颠哥伦比亚大学第一次上了科幻文学课，教师是{{Tsl|en|Susan Wood (science fiction)|苏珊·伍德}}。结课时，他受到鼓励，写下了第一篇短篇小说《[[全息玫瑰碎片_(短篇小说集)|全息玫瑰碎片]]》。<ref name="litencyc"/>

===早期作品与赛博朋克的演化===
吉布森考虑进修硕士并以“作为{{Tsl|en|Fascist (epithet)|法西斯主义 (詈语)|法西斯主义}}文学的[[硬科幻|硬科幻]]”为论题。<ref name="project cyberpunk interview"/>他随后在毕业前一年停止了写作，并据一位批评家称，收集了一些朋克唱片。<ref name="calcutt">{{cite book | last = Calcutt | first = Andrew | title = Cult Fiction | publisher = Contemporary Books | location = Chicago | year = 1999 | isbn = 978-0-8092-2506-4 |oclc = 42363052}}</ref>这段时间他从事了几份不同的工作，包括在母校的一堂电影史课上助教三年。<ref name="litencyc"/>1980年或1981年，吉布森在温哥华一场他看得不耐烦的{{Tsl|en|science fiction convention|科幻展}}上，遇见了同一讨论小组的成员，与他志趣相投的朋克音乐家、作家{{Tsl|en|John Shelly|约翰·雪利}}，<ref name="storming">{{cite book | last = McCaffery | first = Larry | title = Storming the Reality Studio: a casebook of cyberpunk and postmodern science fiction | publisher = [[Duke_University_Press|Duke University Press]] | location = [[Durham,_North_Carolina|Durham, North Carolina]] | year = 1991 | isbn = 978-0-8223-1168-3 | oclc = 23384573}}</ref>两人一见如故，结为一生挚交。雪利说服吉布森，让他出售他的短篇小说，开始认真写作。<ref name="calcutt"/><ref name="storming"/><ref name="calcutt"/><ref name="storming"/>
{{Quote box|align=right|width=30%|1977年，我初为人父，极度缺乏对“事业”这类东西的热情，我开始重拾我十二岁时对科幻文学的兴趣。与此同时，纽约和伦敦传来了奇怪的声音。我认为朋克是社会侧面一颗十年前埋下、引线烧得缓慢的炸弹的爆炸，我认为这预示着什么。就这样，我开始写作了。|salign=right|source=——威廉·吉布森《1948以来》<ref name="sourcecode"/>}}
吉布森通过雪利与科幻作家[[布鲁斯·斯特林|布鲁斯·斯特林]]和{{Tsl|en|Lewis Shiner|刘易斯·夏纳}}取得了联系。他们读了吉布森的作品，发觉这是（斯特林语）“突破性的作品”，需要他们“放下成见，留意一下这温哥华哥们；这可是前进的方向。”<ref name="nomaps"/><ref name="shiner"/>1981年秋天，吉布森在[[科罗拉多州|科罗拉多州]][[丹佛|丹佛]]的科幻展上遇见了斯特林，对着四个人朗读了史上第一篇赛博朋克短篇小说《{{Tsl|en|Burning Chrome|整垮铬萝米}}》；他后来说，斯特林“全明白了”。<ref name="nomaps"/>1982年十月，吉布森前往得克萨斯州奥斯汀参加{{Tsl|en|ArmadilloCon}}科幻展，和雪利、斯特林和夏纳在同一个名叫“镜影之后：一览朋克科幻”（Behind the Mirrorshades: A Look at Punk SF）的讨论小组，夏纳注意到这时“一个运动的概念成形了”。<ref name="shiner">{{cite book | last = Shiner | first = Lewis |author-link=Lewis Shiner |author2=George Edgar Slusser |author3=Tom Shippey  | title = Fiction 2000:Cyberpunk and the Future of Narrative | url = https://archive.org/details/fiction2000cyber0000unse | publisher = University of Georgia Press | location = Athens | year = 1992 | chapter=Inside the Movement: Past, Present and Future |isbn = 978-0-8203-1425-9 |oclc = 24953403}}</ref>在讨论了一星期摇滚、MTV、日本、时尚、毒品、政治这些话题之后，吉布森离开这群讨论小组的骨干回到温哥华，半开玩笑地称“一个新的轴心形成了”。<ref name="shiner"/>斯特林、夏纳、雪利、吉布森和{{Tsl|en|Rudy Rucker|鲁迪·拉克}}后来一同成为了[[赛博朋克|赛博朋克]]这一激进文学运动的核心。<ref>{{cite book| last = Bould| first = Mark| editor = David Seed| title = A Companion to Science Fiction| url = https://archive.org/details/companiontoscien00seed| year = 2005| publisher = Blackwell Publishing Professional| isbn = 978-1-4051-1218-5| oclc = 56924865| pages = [https://archive.org/details/companiontoscien00seed/page/n234 217]–218| chapter = Cyberpunk}}</ref>

==文学生涯==
===早期短篇小说===
{{Further|全息玫瑰碎片 (短篇小说集)}}
吉布森的早期作品，大多数是设定于近未来，探讨控制论和数字空间对人类影响的短篇小说。他所用的高科技[[贫民窟|贫民窟]]、录播的或广播的刺激物（后来发展成在《神经漫游者》中极为着重描写的“模拟-刺激”（Sim-Stig）组合）、反乌托邦中人类与技术和融合这些主题，在他出版的第一篇短篇小说《全息玫瑰碎片》中就已经出现；这篇小说刊载于科幻杂志《出土》 （Unearthed）1977年夏季刊。<ref name="project cyberpunk interview"/>吉布森对”反乌托邦中人类与技术和融合“这一主题的执着被他的朋友和合作者，布鲁斯·斯特林形容为“布鲁斯打出的一套结合高科技和低端生活的经典组合拳。”<ref name=isfdb>{{isfdb name |172}} (ISFDB). Retrieved April 13, 2013.</ref><ref name=mao>{{cite book |last=Gibson |first=William |author2=Bruce Sterling | chapter= Introduction | title=Burning Chrome |year=1986 |publisher=Harper Collins |location=New York |isbn=978-0-06-053982-5 |oclc = 51342671|title-link=Burning Chrome (short story collection) |author2-link=Bruce Sterling }}</ref>1981年开始，<ref name=isfdb/>吉布森的短篇小说始见于《{{Tsl|en|Omni (magazine)|Omni (杂志)|Omni}}》杂志和《Universe 11》杂志中，他收录于其中的作品开始发展出一种苍凉、[[黑色电影|黑色电影]]般的质感。他刻意与主流科幻尽量拉开距离（吉布森对主流科幻“有种美学上的厌恶”，这一点在他的《{{Tsl|en|The Gernsback Continuum|根斯巴克连续体}}》中有体现。），以至于他把最高目标设为成为“一个[[邪典追捧|邪典人物]]，一个小号的[[J·G·巴拉德|J·G·巴拉德]]。”<ref name="project cyberpunk interview"/>斯特林散发这些短篇小说时，发现“他们都懵了……就是说这人写的文章他们都看不懂……他富有想象力的主题大家都不理解。”<ref name="nomaps"/>{{Tsl|en|Larry McCaffery|拉里·麦卡菲里}}评论道，这些早期短篇小说只不过是吉布森写作才能的吉光片羽，科幻评论家{{Tsl|en|Darko Suvin|达科·苏恩文}}则认为它们“无疑是（赛博朋克类型中）最好的作品”，构成了这一艺术类型“最广阔的远景”。<ref name="storming"/>吉布森在这些短篇小说中开发的主题：《{{Tsl|en|Burning Chrome|整垮铬萝米}}》中的蔓生（Sprawl）设定，《{{Tsl|en|Johnny Mnemonics|约翰尼的记忆}}》中的人物{{Tsl|en|Molly Millions|莫莉·米利安斯}}，最终在他的首部长篇小说《[[神经漫游者|神经漫游者]]》中成形。<ref name="storming"/>

===《神经漫游者》===
{{Quote box|align=right|width=40%|港口上空的天色犹如空白电视屏幕。|salign=right|source=—《[[神经漫游者|神经漫游者]]》开篇<ref>{{cite book |author= 威廉·吉布森 |date= 2013-08-01 |title= 神经漫游者 |url= https://cread.jd.com/read/startRead.action?bookId=30227852&readType=1 |others= Denovo译 |publisher= 江苏凤凰文艺 |page= 3 |isbn= 9787539951331 |author-link= 威廉·吉布森 |access-date= 2021-05-24 |archive-date= 2021-04-26 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210426052348/https://cread.jd.com/read/startRead.action?bookId=30227852&readType=1 |dead-url= no }}</ref>}}
《神经漫游者》是受{{Tsl|en|Teddy Carr|泰迪·卡尔}}之托，为专门收录[[处女作|处女作]]的{{Tsl|en|Ace Science Fiction Specials|Ace科幻特辑}}而作的。吉布森完成这部作品的期限是一年，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_09_01_archive.asp#1062520986072822474 |title=Neuromancer: The Timeline |access-date=2007-11-26 |last=Gibson |first=William |date=2003-09-04 |url-status=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061230140902/http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_09_01_archive.asp#1062520986072822474 |archive-date=2006-12-30 }}</ref>在写作过程中，吉布森对完成一部长篇小说这个任务抱有一种“盲目的、本能的恐惧”，他认为他要写出一部长篇小说还“差了四五年”。<ref name="project cyberpunk interview"/>1982年，《[[银翼杀手|银翼杀手]]》上映，吉布森当时写完了整部小说的三分之一；他看了头二十分钟，就“估摸着，（《神经漫游者》）完了，毁了。大家都得觉得我的视觉效果是从这部好看得吓人的电影里边抄的。”<ref name="bladerunner">{{cite web |url=http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_01_01_archive.asp#90199532 |title=Oh Well, While I'm Here: Bladerunner |access-date=2008-01-21 |last=Gibson |first=William |date=2003-01-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070926221513/http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_01_01_archive.asp#90199532 |archive-date=2007-09-26 |url-status=yes }}</ref>吉布森重写了小说的头三分之二十二遍，唯恐读者分神，出版之后，他确信自己要“永永远远地丢脸了”；然而他最终写出的这第一部长篇小说最终大大发展了他的创造力。<ref name="project cyberpunk interview"/>《神经漫游者》刚出版时，并未立刻就广受欢迎，但它迎合了文化潮流，<ref name="hollinger">{{cite journal |last=Hollinger |first=Veronica |date=July 1999 |title=Contemporary Trends in Science Fiction Criticism, 1980–1999 |journal=Science Fiction Studies |volume=26 |issue=78 |url=http://www.depauw.edu/sfs/backissues/78/hollinger78art.htm |access-date=2007-11-06 |archive-date=2007-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071022154814/http://www.depauw.edu/sfs/backissues/78/hollinger78art.htm |url-status=no }}</ref>很快就在另类文化圈中口耳相传，有口皆碑。<ref name="storming"/>《神经漫游者》成为了第一部获得科幻小说“三顶王冠”<ref name="project cyberpunk interview"/>殊荣的作品——它同时获得了[[星云奖|星云奖]]和[[雨果奖|雨果奖]]当年的最佳长篇小说奖，以及[[菲利普·K·迪克纪念奖|菲利普·K·迪克纪念奖]]当年的最佳原创[[平装本|平装本]]奖；<ref name=SFAwards>
[http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/NomLit52.html#1945 "Gibson, William"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101207010245/http://www.locusmag.com/SFAwards/Db/NomLit52.html |date=2010-12-07}}. ''The Locus Index to SF Awards: Index of Literary Nominees''. [[Locus_Publications|Locus Publications]]. Retrieved April 12, 2013.</ref>全球销量累计超过了六百五十万本。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lrc.reviewcanada.ca/index.php?page=71---80 |title=77. Neuromancer (1984) |access-date=2007-09-09 |last=Cheng |first=Alastair |website=The LRC 100: Canada's Most Important Books |publisher=Literary Review of Canada |url-status=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071029044328/http://lrc.reviewcanada.ca/index.php?page=71---80 |archive-date=2007-10-29 }}</ref>1988年，{{Tsl|en|Nova Express (fanzine)|Nova Express (爱好者杂志)|劳伦斯·珀森}}在他的《记后赛博朋克宣言》（Notes Toward a Postcyberpunk Manifesto）中提出，《神经漫游者》是“赛博朋克作品的典范”；<ref name="manifesto">{{cite journal |last=Person |first=Lawrence |date=Winter–Spring 1998 |title=Notes Toward a Postcyberpunk Manifesto |journal=Nova Express |volume=4 |issue=4 |url=http://features.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=99/10/08/2123255 |access-date=2007-11-06 |archive-date=2009-04-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090426022441/http://features.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=99%2F10%2F08%2F2123255 |url-status=no }}</ref>2005年，《[[时代杂志|时代杂志]]》把《神经漫游者》列入1923年以来百部最佳英文小说名单中，并评价道：“（《神经漫游者》）面世时，可谓激进无比。”<ref name="time">{{cite news |url=http://entertainment.time.com/2005/10/16/all-time-100-novels/slide/neuromancer-1984-by-william-gibson/ |title=Neuromancer (1984) |access-date=2007-11-06 |last=Grossman |first=Lev |author2=Richard Lacayo |work=TIME Magazine All-Time 100 Novels |publisher=[[Time_(magazine)|Time]] |date=2005-10-16 |archive-date=2011-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111022173819/http://entertainment.time.com/2005/10/16/all-time-100-novels/slide/neuromancer-1984-by-william-gibson/ |url-status=no }}</ref>文学评论家{{Tsl|en|Larry McCaffery|拉里·麦卡菲里}}把《神经漫游者》中的矩阵描述成这样一个地方：“数据与人类意识共舞……人类记忆是成文的，机械的……跨越国界的信息系统变异增殖，成为惊人的新结构，它有着不可想像的、神秘的，最重要的是，非人的美丽和复杂。”<ref name="project cyberpunk interview"/>吉布森后来评价写作《神经漫游者》时的自己，说：“我肯定请他喝一杯，但钱借不借给他，我就不知道了。”并说这部小说是“青春期著作”。<ref name="nomaps"/>《神经漫游者》获得的成功，使时年三十五岁的吉布森声名鹊起。<ref name="remembering"/>
===《蔓生三部曲》、《差分机》、《桥梁三部曲》===
{{main|{{Tsl|en|Sprawl trilogy|蔓生三部曲}}|差分机 (小说)|{{Tsl|en|Bridge trilogy|桥梁三部曲}}}}
[[File:Cables_in_Virtual_Light.jpg|thumb]]，吉布森《{{Tsl|en|Bridge trilogy|桥梁三部曲}}》设定地点的原型，在小说中被[[占屋|占用]]]]
尽管吉布森的声誉主要源于《神经漫游者》，他仍然改进着他作品的概念和风格。<ref name="spike"/>他本打算新写一部毫不相干的后现代[[太空歌剧|太空歌剧]]，题为《野马莎莉的日志》（The Log of the Mustang Sally），与{{Tsl|en|Arbor House}}出版社签了合同；但随后吉布森与出版社就《零伯爵》[[护封|护封]]的配图一事意见不合，以至于闹翻，吉布森于是毁约。<ref name="mustang">{{cite web |url=http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2005_08_01_archive.asp#112417337358385397 |title=The Log of the Mustang Sally |access-date=2008-01-21 |last=Gibson |first=William |date=2005-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080208235435/http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2005_08_01_archive.asp#112417337358385397 |archive-date=2008-02-08 |url-status=yes }}</ref>放弃《野马莎莉的日志》后，吉布森在1988年写下《{{Tsl|en|Mona Lisa Overdrive|重启蒙娜丽莎}}》。<ref name="project cyberpunk interview"/><ref name="storming"/>这部长篇小说续写吉布森的前两部长篇小说，达到剧情上的高潮，沿用了[[虚拟世界|世界观]]和人物，是《{{Tsl|en|Sprawl trilogy|蔓生三部曲}}》的终篇。《蔓生三部曲》确立了吉布森的声誉，<ref name="citizenship"/>三部曲后续的两部小说，也都获得了星云奖、雨果奖和轨迹科幻奖的提名。<ref name="WWEND=1986">{{cite web |url= http://www.worldswithoutend.com/books_year_index.asp?year=1986 |title= 1986 Award Winners & Nominees |website= Worlds Without End |access-date= 2009-04-30 |archive-date= 2016-04-11 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160411232428/https://www.worldswithoutend.com/books_year_index.asp?year=1986 |url-status= no }}</ref><ref name="WWEND=1987">{{cite web |url= http://www.worldswithoutend.com/books_year_index.asp?year=1987 |title= 1987 Award Winners & Nominees |website= Worlds Without End |access-date= 2009-04-30 |archive-date= 2012-03-22 |archive-url= https://www.webcitation.org/66LUgniWb?url=https://www.worldswithoutend.com/books_year_index.asp?year=1987 |url-status= no }}</ref><ref name="WWEND=1989">{{cite web |url= http://www.worldswithoutend.com/books_year_index.asp?year=1989 |title= 1989 Award Winners & Nominees |website= Worlds Without End |access-date= 2009-04-30 |archive-date= 2017-02-20 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170220110325/https://www.worldswithoutend.com/books_year_index.asp?year=1989 |url-status= no }}</ref>1990年，吉布森继《蔓生三部曲》之后和[[布鲁斯·斯特林|布鲁斯·斯特林]]合作写下了[[架空历史|架空历史]]小说《[[差分机_(小说)|差分机]]》，背景设于科技发达的[[维多利亚时代|维多利亚时代]]英国，背离了吉布森一贯以来的赛博朋克主题。1991年，《差分机》获得了[[星云奖最佳长篇小说奖|星云奖最佳长篇小说奖]]提名；随后于1992年获得了{{Tsl|en|John W. Campbell Memorial Award|约翰·W·坎贝尔纪念奖}}提名。这部小说的成功使新生的[[蒸汽朋克|蒸汽朋克]]文学门类受到关注，它也是这一门类最著名的作品。<ref name="steampunkt">{{cite news | first = Peter | last = Bebergal | title = The age of steampunk | url = https://www.boston.com/news/globe/ideas/articles/2007/08/26/the_age_of_steampunk/ | work = The Boston Globe | page = 3 | date = 2007-08-26 | access-date = 2007-10-14 | archive-date = 2007-09-04 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070904001109/http://www.boston.com/news/globe/ideas/articles/2007/08/26/the_age_of_steampunk/ | url-status = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/booksblog/2009/jan/07/steampunk-chiang-lake-macleod |work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]] |title=Steampunk: the future of the past |first=Damien G |last=Walter |date=2009-01-07 |access-date=2009-01-11 |publisher=Guardian Media Group |location=London |archive-date=2019-04-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190407094132/https://www.theguardian.com/books/booksblog/2009/jan/07/steampunk-chiang-lake-macleod |url-status=no }}</ref>吉布森的第二部系列小说《{{Tsl|en|Bridge trilogy|桥梁三部曲}}》包括著于1993年的“黑色幽默都市侦探短篇小说”<ref name="cyberhero"/>《{{Tsl|en|Virtual Light|虚拟之光}}》、著于1996年的《{{Tsl|en|Idoru|伊朵儿}}》、以及著于1999年的《{{Tsl|en|All Tomorrow's Parties (novel)|All Tomorrow's Parties|明日之星}}》。三部曲中，第一部和第三部小说均以近未来洛杉矶为中心。整部三部曲都用比上一步三部曲更脚踏实地、实事求是的风格探讨了吉布森小说中常见的身心和技术的超越这些主题。<ref name="playboy">{{cite web |url=http://www.playboy.com/arts-entertainment/reviews/books/spook-country/spook-country.html |title=Spook Country |access-date=2007-11-06 |last=Alexander |first=Scott |date=2007-08-09 |website=[[Playboy.com|Playboy.com]] |url-status=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080705154050/http://www.playboy.com/arts-entertainment/reviews/books/spook-country/spook-country.html |archive-date=2008-07-05 }}</ref>{{Tsl|en|Salon (Website)|沙龙 (网站)|沙龙网}}记者{{Tsl|en|Andrew Leonard|安德鲁·莱昂纳德}}提到，在《桥梁三部曲中》，吉布森把笔下的反派从《蔓生三部曲》中的跨国公司和[[人工智能|人工智能]]换成了大众媒体：具体而言，就是{{Tsl|en|tabloid journalism|庸俗新闻|庸俗}}电视和{{Tsl|en|cult of celebrity|名声崇拜}}。<ref name="salonarchy">{{cite web |url=http://www.salon.com/books/feature/1999/07/27/macleod_interview/ |title=An engine of anarchy |last=Leonard |first=Andrew |date=1999-07-27 |website=[[Salon.com|Salon.com]] |url-status=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080108121005/http://www.salon.com/books/feature/1999/07/27/macleod_interview/ |archive-date=2008-01-08 |access-date=2021-05-24 }}</ref>一条评论称，《虚拟之光》描绘的是“资本主义末期，私人企业和利润导向发展至其理论极点”。<ref name="mail&guardian"/>认为大众媒体是资本主义自然演化的产物这一论点在[[情境主义|情境主义]]著作《[[景观社会|景观社会]]》开篇即有提及。莱昂纳德评论《伊朵儿》，称它是吉布森“重返巅峰”之作，<ref name="whither cyberpunk">{{cite web |url=http://www.salon.com/1998/09/14/books_26/ |title=Is cyberpunk still breathing? |access-date=2007-11-06 |last=Leonard |first=Andrew |date=1998-09-14 |website=[[Salon.com|Salon.com]] |archive-date=2014-07-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714202715/http://www.salon.com/1998/09/14/books_26/ |url-status=no }}</ref>而评论家{{Tsl|en|Stephen Poole|史蒂芬·普尔}}则称《明日之星》标志着吉布森从“科幻大神到蹩脚近未来社会学家”的转变。<ref name="nearing"/>
===蓝蚂蚁===
继《明日之星》后，吉布森的文风更加倾向[[现实主义|现实主义]]，保持叙事的连续性，是“猜想极近过去的虚构作品。”<ref name="dueben">{{cite web |url=http://calitreview.com/2007/10/02/william-gibson-the-father-of-cyberpunk/ |title=An Interview With William Gibson The Father of Cyberpunk |access-date=2007-10-04 |last=Dueben |first=Alex |date=2007-10-02 |website=California Literary Review |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071011224147/http://calitreview.com/2007/10/02/william-gibson-the-father-of-cyberpunk/ |archive-date=2007-10-11 |url-status=yes }}</ref>科幻评论家{{Tsl|en|John Clute|约翰·克卢特}}把这种写作角度解释为吉布森对传统科幻在“一个没有可续的‘现在’的世界”中不再可能实现的认识，把这种角度定性为“新世纪的科幻”。<ref name="clute">{{cite web |url=http://www.scifi.com/sfw/issue305/excess.html |title=The Case of the World |last=Clute |first=John |author-link=John Clute |access-date=2007-10-14 |website=Excessive Candour |publisher=SciFi.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071030090441/http://www.scifi.com/sfw/issue305/excess.html |archive-date=2007-10-30 |url-status=yes }}</ref>吉布森的长篇小说《[[模式识别_(小说)|模式识别]]》（2003）、《{{Tsl|en|Spook Country|幽灵山村}}》（2007）、《{{Tsl|en|Zero History|零历史}}》（2010）都把背景设定于当代，“差不多就是我们生活的那个”世界，<ref name="spook-country">{{cite journal |url=https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,1759,2080922,00.asp |title=Q&A: William Gibson |first=Angela |last=Chang |journal=[[PC_Magazine|PC Magazine]] |volume=26 |issue=3 |date=2007-01-10 |page=19 |access-date=2017-09-18 |archive-date=2009-05-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090501223323/http://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,1759,2080922,00.asp |url-status=no }}</ref>这也让吉布森的作品首次成为了主流畅销书。<ref>{{cite news |title = Books: Hardbacks|last = Hirst|first = Christopher|date = 2003-05-10|work = [[The_Independent|The Independent]]}}</ref>在设定相同的同时，这几部小说也有一些共同的人物，如神秘的营销公司蓝蚂蚁的雇员{{Tsl|en|Hubertus Bigend|胡伯特斯·比根德}}、帕梅拉·曼瓦林等。

[[File:William_Gibson_Zero_History_signing_at_Forbidden_Planet_London.jpg|thumb]]

吉布森回答[[推特|推特]]上对这一系列小说的名称的提问（“《比根德三部曲》？《蓝蚂蚁系列》？到底叫啥呢？”）时，说“我还是喜欢‘丛书’，就《比根德丛书》吧。”<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gibson|first1=William|title=23:28 - 7 okt. 2010|url=https://twitter.com/greatdismal/status/26724447356|website=Twitter|access-date=2017-11-26|archive-date=2021-03-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210307213332/https://twitter.com/greatdismal/status/26724447356|url-status=no}}</ref>然而，“蓝蚂蚁”却成为了这一系列的通称。<ref>{{cite web|title=Blue Ant Series|url=https://www.goodreads.com/series/50543-blue-ant|website=Goodreads|access-date=2017-11-26|archive-date=2021-04-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210419035455/https://www.goodreads.com/series/50543-blue-ant|url-status=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Blue Ant Book Series|url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/bookseries/B00CJ2XUKO/|website=Amazon|access-date=2017-11-26|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308033141/https://www.amazon.com/gp/bookseries/B00CJ2XUKO/|url-status=no}}</ref>后来，吉布森称他没有为这三部曲命名，说“我等着看别人怎么叫它呢”，<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gibson|first1=William|title=19:26 - 30 dec. 2012|url=https://twitter.com/GreatDismal/status/285587655192887297|website=Twitter|access-date=2017-11-26|archive-date=2021-03-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210307231356/https://twitter.com/GreatDismal/status/285587655192887297|url-status=no}}</ref>2016年，也在一则推文中用了“《蓝蚂蚁丛书》”一名。<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gibson|first1=William|title=11:46 - 9 juli 2016|url=https://twitter.com/GreatDismal/status/751850008442380288|website=Twitter|access-date=2017-11-26|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308042121/https://twitter.com/GreatDismal/status/751850008442380288|url-status=no}}</ref>

这一时期独特地出现了独立发展的同人注解网站，模识宅（PR-Otaku）和{{Tsl|en|Node Magazine|节点杂志}}，分别批注《模式识别》和《幽灵山村》这两部作品。<ref name="looking glass"/>这两个网站利用[[维基百科|维基百科]]、[[谷歌|谷歌]]等网络资源，考据引据来源、故事要素，并整合所得，相当于编纂了两部书的[[超文本|超文本]]版。<ref name="looking glass"/><ref name="now romancer">{{cite web |url=http://www.salon.com/books/int/2007/08/11/william_gibson/index.html |title=Now Romancer |access-date=2007-10-30 |last=Lim |first=Dennis |date=2007-08-11 |website=[[Salon.com|Salon.com]] |url-status=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080501224918/http://www.salon.com/books/int/2007/08/11/william_gibson/index.html |archive-date=2008-05-01 }}</ref>评论家{{Tsl|en|John Sutherland (author)|John Sutherland|约翰·苏特兰}}认为这种现象恐将“重构文学评论的方式”。<ref name="node idea">{{cite news |first=John |last=Sutherland |author-link=John Sutherland (author) |title=Node idea |url=http://books.guardian.co.uk/comment/story/0,,2159309,00.html |work=[[Guardian_Unlimited|Guardian Unlimited]] |publisher=Guardian Media Group |date=2007-08-31 |access-date=2007-11-11 |location=London |archive-date=2007-09-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070906202236/http://books.guardian.co.uk/comment/story/0,,2159309,00.html |url-status=no }}</ref>。[[911事件|911事件]]发生之后，写完了《模式识别》一百多页的吉布森忽然认为主角的背景故事已经变得不可信，不得不把这一部分重写了一遍；他称这是“我对一部小说最奇特的体验。”<ref>{{cite news |first=Dennis |last=Lim |title=Think Different |url=https://www.villagevoice.com/2003/02/11/think-different/ |work=[[The_Village_Voice|The Village Voice]] |publisher=[[Village_Voice_Media|Village Voice Media]] |date=2003-02-18 |access-date=2019-05-30 |archive-date=2019-05-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190530124400/https://www.villagevoice.com/2003/02/11/think-different/ |url-status=no }}</ref>他认为这场袭击是历史的一个节点，是“一种跳出文化的体验”，并且“在某种意义上……是21世纪的真正开始。”<ref name="smh">{{cite web |url=https://www.smh.com.au/news/books/a-reality-stranger-than-fiction/2007/09/06/1188783376158.html |title=A reality stranger than fiction |access-date=2008-01-21 |last=Bennie |first=Angela |date=2007-09-07 |website=[[Sydney_Morning_Herald|Sydney Morning Herald]] |publisher=Fairfax Media |archive-date=2007-09-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070911031016/http://www.smh.com.au/news/books/a-reality-stranger-than-fiction/2007/09/06/1188783376158.html |url-status=no }}</ref>他是第一位写出受911事件影响的长篇小说的作家，因此受到注意。<ref name="vancouver"/>对911事件后美国文化的转变，包括{{Tsl|en|tribalism|部族主义}}的复兴、“社会{{Tsl|en|Infantilization|婴儿化}}”<ref>{{cite web |url=https://thetyee.ca/Books/2007/10/18/WillGibson/ |title=William Gibson Hates Futurists |access-date=2007-10-26 |website=TheTyee.ca |date=2007-10-18 |archive-date=2007-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071026022040/http://thetyee.ca/Books/2007/10/18/WillGibson/ |url-status=no }}</ref><ref name=actusf/>等的观察成为了日后吉布森作品的重要主题。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/bc/bookclub/williamgibson2.html |title=William Gibson with Spook Country |access-date=2007-10-26 |work=Studio One Bookclub |publisher=CBC British Columbia |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071013220206/http://www.cbc.ca/bc/bookclub/williamgibson2.html |archive-date=2007-10-13 |dead-url=no }}</ref>不过，他写作的重心仍然“处于偏执和技术的焦点”。<ref name="projo">{{cite web |url=http://www.projo.com/books/content/BOOK-GIBSON_09-16-07_376TE7P.53f53f.html |title=Gibson still scares up a spooky atmosphere |access-date=2007-10-26 |website=[[Providence_Journal|Providence Journal]] |url-status=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080116112214/http://www.projo.com/books/content/BOOK-GIBSON_09-16-07_376TE7P.53f53f.html |archive-date=2008-01-16 }}</ref>
=== 头彩丛书 ===
2014年10月28日，吉布森新系列小说的第一部《[[边缘世界|边缘世界]]》发表。<ref>{{cite news |first=Robin |last=Sloan |newspaper=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]] |title=William Gibson's 'The Peripheral' stars a plucky female gamer with 3D printing skills |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/books/william-gibsons-the-peripheral-stars-a-plucky-female-gamer-with-3d-printing-skills/2014/10/27/0dcf3eee-54b1-11e4-892e-602188e70e9c_story.html |date=2014-10-27 |access-date=2014-10-28 |archive-date=2014-10-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141028120055/http://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/books/william-gibsons-the-peripheral-stars-a-plucky-female-gamer-with-3d-printing-skills/2014/10/27/0dcf3eee-54b1-11e4-892e-602188e70e9c_story.html |url-status=no }}</ref> 2013年4月19日，他在纽约公立图书馆露面，对小说做了简短的描述，并朗读了第一章《触觉回馈装置》的选段。<ref>{{cite web |last=Fenlon |first=Wesley |url=http://www.tested.com/art/makers/455051-william-gibson-talks-sci-fi-and-his-next-novel-new-york-public-library/ |title=William Gibson Talks Sci-Fi and His Next Novel at New York Public Library |publisher=Tested |date=2013-04-24 |access-date=2014-04-08 |archive-date=2013-12-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131220181941/http://www.tested.com/art/makers/455051-william-gibson-talks-sci-fi-and-his-next-novel-new-york-public-library/ |url-status=no }}</ref>故事发生在两个不同的年代：其一在距今三十年后的未来，其二在更远的未来。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://io9.com/watch-william-gibson-read-from-his-brand-new-science-fi-484885010 |title=Watch William Gibson read from his brand new science fiction novel |publisher=[[io9|io9]] |date=2013-04-29 |access-date=2014-04-08 |archive-date=2015-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151022150351/http://io9.com/watch-william-gibson-read-from-his-brand-new-science-fi-484885010 |url-status=no }}</ref>《边缘世界》的续作《{{Tsl|en|Agency (novel)|机构 (小说)|机构}}》原定于2018年12月份发表，后推迟到2021年1月21日方发表。<ref>Compare https://www.amazon.com/Agency-William-Gibson/dp/110198693X/ref=sr_1_1?keywords=agency+william+gibson&qid=1554137189&s=gateway&sr=8-1 {{Wayback|url=https://www.amazon.com/Agency-William-Gibson/dp/110198693X/ref=sr_1_1?keywords=agency+william+gibson&qid=1554137189&s=gateway&sr=8-1 |date=20210419035408 }} with https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/530536/agency-by-william-gibson/9781101986936/ {{Wayback|url=https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/530536/agency-by-william-gibson/9781101986936/ |date=20181018201703 }}</ref>据《纽约客》杂志上发表的一篇文章称，特朗普当选和剑桥分析公司引发的争议都让他重新思考文本，对其进行修改。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2019/12/16/how-william-gibson-keeps-his-science-fiction-real|title=How William Gibson Keeps His Science Fiction Real|last=Rothman|first=Joshua|magazine=The New Yorker|date=2019-12-09|access-date=2019-12-16|language=en|issn=0028-792X|archive-date=2019-12-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191216061628/https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2019/12/16/how-william-gibson-keeps-his-science-fiction-real|url-status=no}}</ref>2020年7月17日，吉布森发推特说：“第三/完结篇暂定名称：头彩”，<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gibson |first1=William |title=Third/final volume's working title: Jackpot |url=https://twitter.com/GreatDismal/status/1284226125804138497 |website=Twitter |access-date=2020-09-06 |archive-date=2020-08-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200814142213/https://twitter.com/GreatDismal/status/1284226125804138497 |url-status=no }}</ref>但2021年1月21日又收回前言，称“我还是不给《机构》的续作起名叫《头彩》了。不是因为（迈克尔·梅卡尼克的《头彩》），这本书我还打算读一下，而是因为《机构》原本叫《Tulpagochi》。这名字我还是很喜欢，但那就不是同一本书了。”<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gibson |first1=William |title=I don't think I'm going to call Agency's sequel Jackpot after all |url=https://twitter.com/GreatDismal/status/1352852569593286657 |website=Twitter |access-date=2021-02-19 |archive-date=2021-01-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210123053618/https://twitter.com/GreatDismal/status/1352852569593286657 |url-status=no }}</ref>

===视觉小说===
2017年，《边缘世界》出版之后，《机构》出版之前，吉布森的漫画（或曰视觉小说）《{{Tsl|en|Archangel (Gibson comic)|大天使 (威廉·吉布森漫画)|大天使}}》出版。《大天使》和《边缘世界》都包括了各种时间旅行，但吉布森澄清道，这两部作品并无关联：“它们不是‘同一宇宙’的。撕裂者（The Splitter）和超连续虚拟性（trans-continual virtuality）不是一种装置（也不是同一种情节装置）。”<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gibson|first1=William|title=To readers of both The Peripheral and Archangel|url=https://twitter.com/GreatDismal/status/930113645840707585|website=Twitter|access-date=2017-11-18|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308042137/https://twitter.com/GreatDismal/status/930113645840707585|url-status=no}}</ref>次年，[[黑马漫画|黑马漫画]]分五卷发行约翰尼·克里斯马斯（Johnny Christmas）改编自吉布森的《异形3》剧本的同名漫画，<ref>{{cite web |last1=Terror |first1=Jude |title=Johnnie Christmas to Adapt William Gibson's Unpublished Aliens 3 Script as a Comic Book |url=https://bleedingcool.com/comics/johnnie-christmas-adapt-william-gibson-aliens-3-script-comic-book/ |website=Bleeding Cool |access-date=2020-09-06 |archive-date=2020-11-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109015424/https://bleedingcool.com/comics/johnnie-christmas-adapt-william-gibson-aliens-3-script-comic-book/ |url-status=no }}</ref>2019年出版精装合集。<ref>{{cite web |last1=Conner |first1=Shawn |title=Join William Gibson and Johnnie Christmas for a special launch of their book Alien 3! |url=https://www.insidevancouver.ca/2019/08/13/william-gibson-johnnie-christmas-special-launch-alien-3/ |website=Inside Vancouver |access-date=2020-09-06 |archive-date=2020-08-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803212109/https://www.insidevancouver.ca/2019/08/13/william-gibson-johnnie-christmas-special-launch-alien-3/ |url-status=no }}</ref>

==合作，改编及其他==
[[File:Bruce_Sterling_sn-ed.jpg|thumb]]，与吉布森合著了短篇小说 《{{Tsl|en|Red Star, Winter Orbit|红星，冬季轨道}}》（1983）和蒸汽朋克长篇小说《[[差分机_(小说)|差分机]]》（1990）]]
===文学合作===
《[[全息玫瑰碎片_(短篇小说集)|全息玫瑰碎片]]》日后收录的短篇小说中，有三篇是吉布森与他人合著的：1981年与{{Tsl|en|John Shelly|约翰·雪利}}合著的《{{Tsl|en|The Belonging Kind|酒吧里的归栖者}}》、1983年与[[布鲁斯·斯特林|布鲁斯·斯特林]]合著的《{{Tsl|en|Red Star, Winter Orbit|红星，冬季轨道}}》<ref name="looking glass">{{cite news |first=Joel |last=Garreau |title=Through the Looking Glass |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/09/05/AR2007090502582_pf.html |work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]] |date=2007-09-06 |access-date=2007-10-30 |archive-date=2016-08-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160805223007/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/09/05/AR2007090502582_pf.html |url-status=no }}</ref>、以及同年与{{Tsl|en|Michael Swanwick|迈克尔·斯万维克}}合著的《{{Tsl|en|Dogfight (short story)|空战 (短篇小说)|空战}}》。吉布森此前为雪利1980年出版的长篇小说《城市走过来了》（City Come A-walkin{{'}}）写了前言，<ref name="ftccaw">{{cite web|url=http://www.darkecho.com/JohnShirley/gibson.html|title=Foreword to ''City Come a-walkin{{'}}''|date=1996-03-31|access-date=2007-05-01|first=William|last=Gibson|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070626031709/http://www.darkecho.com/JohnShirley/gibson.html|archive-date=2007-06-26|url-status=yes}}</ref>两人随后继续合作，吉布森又为雪利1989年出版的短篇小说集《寻热者》（Heatseeker）写了前言。<ref name="locusmag">{{cite web |url = http://www.locusmag.com/index/s296.html |title = Stories, Listed by Author |access-date = 2007-10-29 |last = Brown |first = Charles N. |author-link = Charles N. Brown |author2 = William G. Contento |date = 2004-07-10 |website = The Locus Index to Science Fiction (1984–1998) |publisher = [[Locus_(magazine)|Locus]] |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070304205021/http://www.locusmag.com/index/s296.html |archive-date = 2007-03-04 |dead-url = no }}</ref>雪利说服吉布森，让他给电视系列节目《{{Tsl|en|Max Headroom (TV series)|双面麦斯}}》写一段剧情；但写好之前，电视网就把节目取消了。<ref name="salza"/>1990年，吉布森与斯特林合著短篇小说《歌利亚的天使》，<ref name="locusmag"/>不久后扩写为长篇架空历史小说《差分机》，成书于1990年。1993年，两人被请去“公开做梦”（吉布森语），共同为[[美国国家科学院|美国国家科学院]]技术与教育大会（“[[阿尔·戈尔|阿尔·戈尔]]他们”<ref name="salza"/>）致辞反对[[数位落差|数位落差]]<ref>{{cite web |url = http://w2.eff.org/Misc/Publications/William_Gibson/sterling_gibson_nas.speeches |title = Speeches by William Gibson and Bruce Sterling at the National Academy of Sciences, Washington, D.C |access-date = 2007-10-29 |last = Sterling |first = Bruce |author-link = Bruce Sterling |author2 = William Gibson |date = 1993-05-10 |publisher = The [[WELL_(virtual_community)|WELL]] |url-status = yes |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20081027165055/http://w2.eff.org/Misc/Publications/William_Gibson/sterling_gibson_nas.speeches |archive-date = 2008-10-27 }}</ref>，“震惊全场”地提议把所有学校设在线上、通过互联网进行教育。<ref name="josefsson"/>2007年接受采访时，吉布森透露斯特林正在构思“第二部递归科幻小说，想法极好”，但吉布森正有其他创作，无法与斯特林合作。<ref name="dueben"/>1993年，吉布森为[[黄色魔术交响乐团|黄色魔术交响乐团]]的专辑《{{Tsl|en|Technodon|Technodon}}》作词，并且受邀为主唱。<ref name="skier"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.discogs.com/release/432896 |title=Yellow Magic Orchestra – Technodon |access-date=2008-01-10 |website=[[Discogs|Discogs]] |archive-date=2008-02-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080225162911/http://www.discogs.com/release/432896 |url-status=no }}</ref>同年，吉布森又为黛比·哈利的专辑《{{Tsl|en|Debravation|Debravation}}》中的音轨《Dog Star Girl》作词。<ref name="debravation">{{cite news |first=Degen |last=Pener |title=EGOS & IDS; Deborah Harry Is Low-Key – And Unblond |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9F0CE6DC1239F931A1575BC0A965958260&n=Top/Reference/Times%20Topics/People/H/Harry,%20Debbie |work=The New York Times |date=1993-08-22 |access-date=2007-11-07 |archive-date=2021-04-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210419035408/https://www.nytimes.com/1993/08/22/style/egos-ids-deborah-harry-is-low-key-and-unblond.html |url-status=no }}</ref>

===电影改编、剧本、出镜===
吉布森开始受邀写电影剧本的契机，是一位制片人在泰国一处度假村的海滩上发现了一本浸了水的《神经漫游者》。<ref>{{cite journal |journal=[[Details_(magazine)|Details]] |url=http://www.textfiles.com/sf/cyberlit.txt |title=Cyber Lit |date=June 1992 |first=Gavin |last=Edwards |issue=134 |access-date=2008-09-29 |archive-date=2008-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080924005406/http://www.textfiles.com/sf/cyberlit.txt |url-status=no }}</ref>吉布森早期的电影剧本最终都未能成形：《整垮铬萝米》（原定由[[凯瑟琳·毕格罗|凯瑟琳·毕格罗]]导演）和《神经旅馆》（Neuro-Hotel）两部改编电影最终都未能制作。<ref name="salza">{{cite interview |last=Gibson |first=William |title=William Gibson Interviewed by Giuseppe Salza |location=Cannes |date=May 1994 |url=https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/235 |access-date=October 28, 2007 |archive-date=2011-10-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111011104756/http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/235 |url-status=no }}</ref>1980年代末，吉布森写下了《[[异形3|异形3]]》的一个（后来自评为“像[[塔尔科夫斯基|塔尔科夫斯基]]”的）早期版本，其中只有几处在定稿中得以保留。<ref name="salza"/>2018到19年，黑马漫画把这部剧本改编为漫画，共五部，由约翰尼·克里斯马斯编绘。2019年，{{Tsl|en|Audible (service)|Audible}}把这部剧本制作成广播剧，由{{Tsl|en|Dirk Maggs|德克·马格斯}}改编，[[迈克尔·比恩|迈克尔·比恩]]和[[兰斯·亨利克森|兰斯·亨利克森]]出演他们在电影中饰演的角色。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://soundcloud.com/audible/alien-3-teaser |title=Alien III Teaser |access-date=2019-04-29 |archive-date=2019-05-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190501141659/https://soundcloud.com/audible/alien-3-teaser |url-status=no }}</ref>吉布森初涉电影产业时，就已经不受好莱坞大片体系的限制。在一位美国制片人表达意向，要制作一部苏美合拍、由苏联摇滚乐手[[维克多·崔|维克多·崔]]出演的电影后，他一度与哈萨克斯坦导演{{Tsl|en|Rashid Nugmanov|拉希德·努格马诺夫}}合作剧本。<ref name="victor tsoi">{{cite web |url=http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_03_01_archive.asp#90416069 |title=Victor Tsoi |access-date=2007-12-03 |last=Gibson |first=William |date=2003-03-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071210172807/http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_03_01_archive.asp#90416069 |archive-date=2007-12-10 |url-status=yes }}</ref>吉布森当时忙于创作小说，但不愿放弃这一包括了“在某种平行未来的[[列宁格勒|列宁格勒]]的群殴仪式”的“怪得绝妙的项目”，于是派{{Tsl|en|Jack Womack|杰克·沃马克}}去俄罗斯接班。由于崔遭遇车祸身亡，电影并未拍成。沃马克最终根据在俄罗斯的经历写了一部长篇小说，《{{Tsl|en|Let's Put the Future Behind Us|把未来抛在身后吧}}》，这段经历也影响了吉布森的《[[模式识别_(小说)|模式识别]]》一书中与俄罗斯有关的部分。<ref name="victor tsoi"/>1991年吉布森与日本导演{{Tsl|en|Sogo Ishii|石井岳龙|石井聪亘}}的合作同样未能成功，<ref name="storming"/>两人本打算在[[九龙寨城|九龙寨城]]拍摄一部电影，结果1993年，九龙寨城就拆毁了。<ref name="sogo">{{cite web |url=http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2006_07_01_archive.asp#115354123358489417 |title=Burst City Trailer |first=William |last=Gibson |date=2006-07-21 |access-date=2007-11-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071121223044/http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2006_07_01_archive.asp#115354123358489417 |archive-date=2007-11-21 |url-status=yes }}</ref>
[[File:The_Neuromancer.jpg|thumb]]
吉布森的小说常被改编，却并不非常成功。吉布森《{{Tsl|en|Sprawl trilogy|蔓生三部曲}}》世界观下的两部短篇小说，曾大致遵照原著，被改编成电影：其一是1995年的《{{Tsl|en|Johnny Mnemonics (film)|捍卫机密}}》，由《约翰尼的记忆》改编，吉布森编剧，基努·里维斯、道夫·龙格尔、[[北野武|北野武]]出演；另一部是1998年的《{{Tsl|en|New Rose Hotel (film)|新玫瑰旅馆 (电影)|新玫瑰旅馆}}》，由同名小说改编，克里斯托弗·沃肯、威廉·达福、艾莎·阿基多出演。其中，《捍卫机密》是史上第一部与其原著改编的CD-ROM互动式电子游戏同时面世的电影。<ref name="mail&guardian">{{cite web |url=http://mg.co.za/article/1996-09-03-blade-runner-on-electrosteroids |title=Blade Runner on electro-steroids |access-date=2007-11-11 |last=Walker |first=Martin |date=1996-09-03 |website=[[Mail_&_Guardian#The_Mail_&_Guardian_Online|Mail & Guardian Online]] |publisher=M&G Media |archive-date=2014-07-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714214100/http://mg.co.za/article/1996-09-03-blade-runner-on-electrosteroids |url-status=no }}</ref>截至2013年，尽管经历了数年的[[制作困境|制作困境]]，[[温琴佐·纳塔利|温琴佐·纳塔利]]仍然希望能把《神经漫游者》搬上荧幕。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=39171 |title=Vincenzo Natali Still Hopeful For Neuromancer |date=2013-10-28 |access-date=2014-02-25 |website=Empire |author=Williams, Owen |archive-date=2013-12-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131212232316/http://www.empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=39171 |url-status=no }}</ref>《{{Tsl|en|Count Zero|零伯爵}}》和《{{Tsl|en|Mona Lisa Overdrive|重启蒙娜丽莎}}》也被买下版权，有过改编成电影的计划。<ref name="mtv"/>2006年，消息称《{{Tsl|en|Idoru|伊朵儿}}》的[[日本动画|日本动画]]版已经开工，<ref>{{cite web |url= http://cyberpunkreview.com/movie/upcoming-movies/william-gibsons-idoru-coming-to-anime |date= 2006-04-21 |title= William Gibson's Idoru Coming to Anime |publisher= cyberpunkreview.com |url-status= yes |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20070914195904/http://www.cyberpunkreview.com/movie/upcoming-movies/william-gibsons-idoru-coming-to-anime/ |archive-date= 2007-09-14 |access-date= 2021-05-25 }}</ref> 而《模式识别》的电影版也在制作当中，由[[彼得·威尔|彼得·威尔]]导演；然而，据吉布森称，威尔已不再参与这一企划。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2007_05_01_archive.asp#2514436070772070825 |title=I've Forgotten More Neuromancer Film Deals Than You've Ever Heard Of |access-date=2007-11-04 |last=Gibson |first=William |date=2007-05-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070523100703/http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2007_05_01_archive.asp#2514436070772070825 |archive-date=2007-05-23 |url-status=yes }}</ref>2015年，曾获得英国电影学院奖的作家兼导演{{Tsl|en|Simon Pummell|西蒙·帕梅尔}}在[[鹿特丹影展|鹿特丹影展]]上宣布，计划将吉布森的短篇小说《空战》改编成电影。这部小说由吉布森与{{Tsl|en|Michael Swanwick|迈克尔·斯万维克}}合著，1985年七月首发于《{{Tsl|en|Omni (magazine)|Omni (杂志)|Omni}}》杂志。这部电影计划由Hot Property Films制片公司的英国制片人{{Tsl|en|Janine Marmot|珍宁·马莫特}}制作。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.screendaily.com/news/pummell-preps-william-gibson-adaptation/5082271.article |title=Simon Pummell preps William Gibson adaptation Dogfight |access-date=2015-01-27 |last=Macnab |first=Geoffrey |date=2015-01-27 |archive-date=2015-02-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150202001518/http://www.screendaily.com/news/pummell-preps-william-gibson-adaptation/5082271.article |url-status=no }}</ref>吉布森也经常与他人合作参与电视领域。他与友人{{Tsl|en|Tom Maddox|汤姆·迈达克斯}}共同创作了电视剧《[[X档案|X档案]]》的两集，《{{Tsl|en|Kill Switch (The X-Files)|人工智能 (X档案)|人工智能}}》和《{{Tsl|en|First Person Shooter (The X-Files)|第一人称射击游戏 (X档案)|第一人称射击游戏}}》，分别于1998年和2002年由[[第二十电视公司|二十世纪福克斯电视台]]在美国播出。<ref name="spike"/><ref name=newsbytes>{{cite news |title="X-Files" Writer Fights For Online Privacy |last=Fridman |first=Sherman |date=2000-02-24 |work=News Briefs |publisher=Newsbytes PM}}</ref>1998年，吉布森为《[[X档案|X档案]]》的周边出版物《X档案画集》（The Art of the X-Files）写了前言。<ref>{{cite book |title= The Art of the X-Files|publisher=HarperEntertainment|date=1998-10-07|others= edited by Chris Carter and Carole Kismaric, introduction written by William Gibson|isbn=0061050377}}</ref>在原作者{{Tsl|en|Bruce Wagner|布鲁斯·瓦格纳}}的要求下，吉布森在电视迷你剧《{{Tsl|en|Wild Palms|野棕榈 (电视剧)|野棕榈}}》中客串出演。<ref name="holograms">{{cite web |url=http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2006_07_01_archive.asp#115361118165031237 |title=Where The Holograms Go |first=William |last=Gibson |date=2006-07-22 |access-date=2007-11-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071121223044/http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2006_07_01_archive.asp#115361118165031237 |archive-date=2007-11-21 |url-status=yes }}</ref>《野棕榈》的导演[[奥利弗·斯通|奥利弗·斯通]]在制作这部电视剧时，从吉布森的长篇小说中借用了大量元素，<ref name="cyberhero">{{cite news |first=Adam |last=Platt |title=Cyberhero |url=https://www.newyorker.com/archive/1993/08/16/1993_08_16_024_TNY_CARDS_000364256 |work=The Talk of the Town |publisher=[[The_New_Yorker|The New Yorker]] |date=1993-09-16 |page=24 |access-date=2007-11-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/19990223224043/http://multiweb.evolution.com/clients/mindvox/newyorker.html |archive-date=1999-02-23 |dead-url=no }}</ref>电视剧停播后，吉布森为《野棕榈读本》（Wild Palms Reader）写了一篇文章《全息影像的去处》（Where The Holograms Go）。<ref name="holograms"/>2002年，吉布森又接下一个角色，在短片《{{Tsl|en|Mon Amour Mon Parapluie|我的爱我的伞}}》中与{{Tsl|en|Douglass Coupland|道格拉斯·柯普兰}}一同饰演哲学家。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://64.207.169.13/mamp/cast/cast.htm |title=Cast |access-date=2007-10-26 |website=Mon Amour Mon Parapluie |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040621004844/http://64.207.169.13/mamp/cast/cast.htm |archive-date=2004-06-21 |url-status=yes }}</ref>除出演虚构电影作品之外，吉布森还是2000年由{{Tsl|en|Mark Neale|马克·尼尔}}导演的纪录片《{{Tsl|en|No Maps for These Territories|威廉·吉布森的旅行}}》的主角。这部纪录片给吉布森作传，跟踪吉布森驾车穿越北美大陆，探讨自己人生经历、文学生涯、文化解读的旅程。这部纪录片还包括了对杰克·沃马克和布鲁斯·斯特林的采访，以及[[博诺|博诺]]和[[The_Edge|The Edge]]朗读《神经漫游者》的片段。<ref name="nomaps"/>2016年，加拿大动画工作室Last Studio Standing Inc.买下了吉布森短篇小说《{{Tsl|en|Hinterlands|蛮荒之族}}》的改编权，宣布要将其改编为一部剧场版动画短片和一部电视动画剧集。<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.animationmagazine.net/features/last-studio-standing-bringing-sci-fi-saga-hinterlands-to-screen/?utm_source=feedburner&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=Feed%3A+AnimationMagazine+%28Animation+Magazine%29 |title= Last Studio Standing Bringing Sci-Fi Saga ‘Hinterlands’ to Screen |last= Milligan |first= Mercedes |date= 2017-06-26 |website= Animation Magazine |accessdate= 2021-05-25 |archive-date= 2021-05-25 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210525070751/https://www.animationmagazine.net/features/last-studio-standing-bringing-sci-fi-saga-hinterlands-to-screen/?utm_source=feedburner&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=Feed:+AnimationMagazine+(Animation+Magazine) |dead-url= no }}</ref>截至2018年4月，[[亚马逊公司|亚马逊]]的一部改编自吉布森小说《边缘世界》的[[边缘世界_(电视剧)|电视连续剧]]正在制作当中。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://techcrunch.com/2018/04/17/amazon-william-gibson/ |title=Amazon is developing a TV show based on William Gibson's 'The Peripheral' |access-date=2018-08-31 |archive-date=2018-09-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180901080400/https://techcrunch.com/2018/04/17/amazon-william-gibson/ |url-status=no }}</ref>

===艺术展、诗歌、行为艺术===
