吉布森写作了大量行为艺术作品中使用的文章。1989年十月，吉布森就与著名雕塑家、后来导演了电影《{{Tsl|en|Johnny Mnemonics (film)|捍卫机密}}》的{{Tsl|en|Robert Longo|罗伯特·朗格}}合作，<ref name="remembering">{{cite journal |url=https://www.wired.com/wired/archive/3.06/gibson.html |title=Remembering Johnny |access-date=2008-01-10 |last=van Bakel |first=Rogier |journal=[[Wired_(magazine)|Wired]] |volume=3 |date=June 1995 |issue=6 |archive-date=2008-05-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080516013720/http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/3.06/gibson.html |url-status=no }}</ref>为一个名为“Dream Jumbo: Working the Absolutes”的艺术项目写过这种文章，这一项目在[[加利福尼亚大学洛杉矶分校|加利福尼亚大学洛杉矶分校]]的{{Tsl|en|Royce Hall|罗伊斯礼堂}}展览。<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1989-10-09-ca-23-story.html |title= STAGE REVIEW : A Young Pro Who Knows His Technology |last= Sullivan |first= Dan |date= 1989-10-09 |publisher= Los Angeles Times |accessdate= 2021-05-25 |archive-date= 2021-05-25 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210525101124/https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1989-10-09-ca-23-story.html |dead-url= no }}</ref>三年后，吉布森又为La Fura dels Baus在巴塞罗那举办的Art Futura '92艺术展上的表演秀“记忆宫”（Memory Palace）写了原始文案，表演秀上还使用了{{Tsl|en|Karl Sims|卡尔·西姆斯}}、{{Tsl|en|Rebecca Allen (artist)|丽贝卡·艾伦 (艺术家)|蕾贝卡·艾伦}}、{{Tsl|en|Mark Pellington|马克·佩灵顿}}创作的图片，以及[[彼得·蓋布瑞爾|彼特·盖布瑞尔]]等人创作的音乐。<ref name="skier"/>吉布森在行为艺术方面最新的创作在1997年，与温哥华一支饱受好评的舞团{{Tsl|en|Holy Body Tattoo|圣体纹身}}以及后来和吉布森成为朋友，为他管理网站的克里斯·哈尔克罗（Chris Halcrow）合作。<ref name="holybody">{{cite web |url=http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_05_01_archive.asp#200367789 |title=Holy Body Tattoo |last=Gibson |first=William |date=2003-05-31 |access-date=2007-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071210172818/http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_05_01_archive.asp#200367789 |archive-date=2007-12-10 |url-status=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://archive.nytimes.com/www.nytimes.com/library/cyber/week/031297gibson.html |title=Father of Cyberspace Sires Techno-Naïve Web Sights |last=Ditlea |first=Steve |date=1997-03-12 |access-date=2021-05-28 |url-status=no |archive-date=2021-09-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210921044455/https://archive.nytimes.com/www.nytimes.com/library/cyber/week/031297gibson.html }}</ref>1990年，吉布森参与了“预见旧金山”（Visionary San Francisco）艺术展，这一艺术展设在[[旧金山现代艺术博物馆|旧金山现代艺术博物馆]]，从7月14日举办到8月26日；吉布森为此写了一篇短篇小说《{{Tsl|en|Skinner's Room|斯金纳的房间}}》，设定在日益衰败的旧金山，[[旧金山-奥克兰海湾大桥|旧金山-奥克兰海湾大桥]]关闭后被无家可归者占用，这一设定后在《{{Tsl|en|Bridge trilogy|桥梁三部曲}}》中被详细描写。<ref>{{cite book | last = Polledri | first = Paolo | title = Visionary San Francisco | publisher = Prestal | location = Munich | year = 1990 | oclc = 22115872 | isbn = 978-3-7913-1060-2 | url = https://archive.org/details/visionarysanfran0000poll }}</ref>这一设定启发了由建筑师冯明（音译）（Ming Fung）和克雷格·霍杰茨（Craig Hodgetts）创作的展项，设想在未来的旧金山，富人住在高科技、太阳供能的塔楼里，俯瞰衰朽的城市、破败的大桥的情景。<ref name="architecture"/>这一展项还包括在显示器上显示吉布森探讨未来，朗读《斯金纳的房间》片段的画面。<ref name=skier>{{cite web |url= http://www.skierpage.com/gibson/biblio.htm |title= William Gibson Bibliography / Mediagraphy |access-date= 2008-02-09 |author= S. Page |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20071015154602/http://skierpage.com/gibson/biblio.htm |archive-date= 2007-10-15 |url-status= yes }}</ref>《纽约时报》称赞这次展会为“过去十年内由我国博物馆发起的一次旨趣最高远的，也是最值得称道的，阐释建筑和城市两个领域的努力”，而又评价冯和霍杰茨受吉布森小说影响的展项道：“一件强有力，但悲伤而不无犬儒主义的作品”。<ref name="architecture">{{cite news |first=Paul |last=Goldberger |title=In San Francisco, A Good Idea Falls With a Thud |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9C0CE1DB103CF931A2575BC0A966958260 |work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |date=1990-08-12 |access-date=2007-11-06 |archive-date=2007-10-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071013214418/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9C0CE1DB103CF931A2575BC0A966958260 |url-status=no }}</ref>这部小说后稍作修改，一年后刊登于《{{Tsl|en|Omni (magazine)|Omni (杂志)|Omni}}》杂志。<ref>{{cite journal |last=Gibson |first=William |date=November 1991 |title=Skinner's Room |journal=[[Omni_(magazine)|Omni]] |title-link=Skinner's Room }}</ref>

===密码学===
吉布森的一部特受好评的作品就是1992年的《{{Tsl|en|Agrippa (A Book of the Dead)|阿格里帕（死者之書）}}》，一首三百行的电子自述诗，是吉布森与{{Tsl|en|Dennis Ashbaugh|丹尼斯·阿什鲍}}和发行人小凯文·贝戈斯（Kevin Begos, Jr.）合作的。<ref>{{cite book| last = Liu| first = Alan| title = The laws of cool : knowledge work and the culture of information| url = https://archive.org/details/lawscoolknowledg00liua| date = 2004-06-30| publisher = [[University_of_Chicago_Press|University of Chicago Press]]| location = Chicago| isbn = 978-0-226-48698-7| oclc = 53823956| pages = [https://archive.org/details/lawscoolknowledg00liua/page/n351 339]–48}}</ref>这篇文章聚焦于记忆（标题中的“阿格里帕”就是一本相册的名字）超脱于尘世的特性，原本录入在一张3.5寸[[软盘|软盘]]中，<ref>{{cite web |url= http://agrippa.english.ucsb.edu/post/documents-subcategories/the-disk-and-its-code/original-1992-agrippa-diskette-used-to-make-emulated-run-of-william-gibsons-poem |title= Original 1992 Agrippa Diskette Used to Make Emulated Run of William Gibson’s Poem |website= The Agrippa Files |accessdate= 2021-05-26 |archive-date= 2021-05-26 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210526101156/http://agrippa.english.ucsb.edu/post/documents-subcategories/the-disk-and-its-code/original-1992-agrippa-diskette-used-to-make-emulated-run-of-william-gibsons-poem |dead-url= no }}</ref>附在一本{{Tsl|en|artist's book|艺术家书}}中发行。<ref>{{cite web |url= http://agrippa.english.ucsb.edu/post/home/i-hesitated-before-untying-the-bow-that-held-this-book-together#continued |title= “I hesitated before untying the bow that bound this book together…” |last= Liu |first= Alan |last2= Hehmeyer |first2= Paxton |last3= Hodge |first3= James |last4= Knight |first4= Kimberly |last5= Roh |first5= David |last6= Swanstrom |first6= Elizabeth |website= The Agrippa Files |accessdate= 2021-05-26 |archive-date= 2021-05-26 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210526101203/http://agrippa.english.ucsb.edu/post/home/i-hesitated-before-untying-the-bow-that-held-this-book-together#continued |dead-url= no }}</ref>这本书的内容是阿什鲍作的蚀刻画，本来计划做成光照下逐渐消失的效果，结果未能实现。<ref>{{cite web |url= http://agrippa.english.ucsb.edu/simulation-of-dennis-ashbaughs-fading-ink-concept |title= Simulation of Dennis Ashbaugh’s Fading Ink Concept |website= The Agrippa Files |accessdate= 2021-05-26 |archive-date= 2021-05-26 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210526104249/http://agrippa.english.ucsb.edu/simulation-of-dennis-ashbaughs-fading-ink-concept |dead-url= no }}</ref>吉布森还提到，阿什鲍的设计“后来逐渐发展到包括了一个自我吞噬的软盘，要实现的效果是只显示文字一次，然后就自己把自己吃了。”<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/source/source.asp |title=Introduction to Agrippa: A Book of the Dead |last=Gibson |first=William |year=1992 |access-date=2007-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071120193555/http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/source/source.asp |archive-date=2007-11-20 |url-status=yes }}</ref>与五花八门的说法不同的是，这部作品所用的软盘从没有被“黑”（“hacked”）进去过：在网上广为流传的的诗歌片段，都是从1992年十二月在曼哈顿的一场展示了诗歌内容的公开展览上，通过暗中录下的磁带传播开的：这盘磁带的内容在展览后的第二天，就被上传到{{Tsl|en|MindVox}}布告板上，自此诗歌开始在互联网上广泛传播。<ref>{{cite book| last = Kirschenbaum| first = Matthew G.| title = Mechanisms : new media and the forensic imagination| edition = 2| publisher = [[MIT_Press|MIT Press]]| location = [[Cambridge,_Massachusetts|Cambridge, Massachusetts]]| isbn = 978-0-262-11311-3| oclc = 79256819| access-date = 2007-11-11| chapter = Hacking 'Agrippa': The Source of the Online Text.| chapter-url = http://agrippa.english.ucsb.edu/kirschenbaum-matthew-g-hacking-agrippa-the-source-of-the-online-text/| year = 2008| archive-date = 2007-11-15| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20071115202350/http://agrippa.english.ucsb.edu/kirschenbaum-matthew-g-hacking-agrippa-the-source-of-the-online-text/| url-status = no}}</ref>自1992年首发以来，《阿格里帕》中的秘密隐藏了二十年。很多人都尝试着破解代码、破译代码，但程序的源码很早就散佚了。艾伦·刘（音译）（Alan Liu）率领团队建立了网站阿格里帕文件（The Agrippa Files）<ref>{{cite web |url=http://agrippa.english.ucsb.edu/ |title=The Agrippa Files |website=Agrippa.english.ucsb.edu |access-date=2015-12-09 |archive-date=2011-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111017135609/http://agrippa.english.ucsb.edu/ |url-status=no }}</ref>，广泛收集有助于破解《阿格里帕》代码的工具和资源。他们与{{Tsl|en|Maryland Institute for Technology in the Humanities|马里兰人文技术研究所}}的马修·柯申鲍姆（Matthew Kirschenbaum）、数字法医学实验室（Digital Forensics Lab）、多伦多大学密码学博士生奎因·杜邦（Quinn DuPont）展开合作，向密码学家求助，创立了“破解《阿格里帕》代码挑战”（Cracking the Agrippa Code: The Challenge），开出奖品悬赏破解这段加密诗歌的参与者。<ref>{{cite web | last = Goodin | first = Dan | title = Solve 20-year-old mystery in William Gibson's "Agrippa"; win prizes | url = https://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2012/07/william-gibsons-agrippa-mystery-challenge/ | website = Ars Technica | date = 2012-07-11 | access-date = 2012-07-24 | archive-date = 2012-07-26 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120726224544/http://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2012/07/william-gibsons-agrippa-mystery-challenge/ | url-status = no }}</ref>2012年六月末，代码被罗伯特·萧（音译）（Robert Xiao）成功破解。<ref name=CAG>{{cite web |url=http://www.crackingagrippa.net/ |title=Cracking the Agrippa Code |website=Crackingagrippa.net |date=March 25, 1992 |access-date=December 9, 2015 |archive-date=September 15, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150915184148/http://www.crackingagrippa.net/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===论文和短篇非虚构作品===
吉布森零散地在报刊上发表过一些非虚构文章。他偶尔在《[[连线|连线]]》杂志上刊登几篇长文，为《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》写过几篇[[社论对页版|社论对页版]]，也曾给《[[观察家报|观察家报]]》、《{{Tsl|en|Addicted to Noise|噪声瘾}}》杂志、《{{Tsl|en|New York Times Magazine|纽约时报杂志}}》、《[[滚石_(杂志)|滚石]]》杂志、《{{Tsl|en|Details Magazine|细节杂志}}》供过稿。吉布森首篇重要的非虚构作品《{{Tsl|en|Disneyland with the Death Penalty|有死刑的迪斯尼乐园}}》引起了评论界的热烈反响。<ref name=source>{{cite journal |title=Disneyland with the Death Penalty |url=https://www.wired.com/wired/archive/1.04/gibson.html |last=Gibson |first=William |issue=4 |date=September–October 1993 |journal=[[Wired_(magazine)|Wired]] |volume=1 |access-date=2008-09-23 |archive-date=2008-10-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081001084957/http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/1.04/gibson.html |url-status=no }}</ref><ref name=b&>{{cite news |title=Multimedia Animal Wired Visionary Nicholas Negroponte is MIT's Loud Voice of the Future |date=1995-03-01 |first=David |last=Mehegan |work=[[Boston_Globe|Boston Globe]] |publisher=[[The_New_York_Times_Company|The New York Times Company]] |url=https://secure.pqarchiver.com/boston/doc/290733867.html |access-date=2008-09-23 |archive-date=2015-04-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402131744/https://secure.pqarchiver.com/boston/doc/290733867.html |url-status=no }}</ref>2003年一月起，吉布森开始创作博客，就他对他本人当时的新作小说《[[模式识别_(小说)|模式识别]]》的反应提供“窥视般的见解”；但同年九月，吉布森就因为担心可能影响创作，不再更新博客了。<ref name="orlowski">{{cite news |first=Andrew |last=Orlowski |title=William Gibson 'gives up blogging' |url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2003/04/25/william_gibson_gives_up_blogging/ |work=Music and Media |publisher=The Register |date=2003-04-25 |access-date=2007-11-03 |archive-date=2007-08-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070814104508/http://www.theregister.co.uk/2003/04/25/william_gibson_gives_up_blogging/ |url-status=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last        = Gibson|first        = William|url        = http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_09_01_archive.asp#1062520986072822474|publisher        = WilliamGibsonBooks.com|title        = Endgame|date        = 2003-09-12|access-date        = 2007-11-26|url-status        = yes|archive-url        = https://web.archive.org/web/20061230140902/http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_09_01_archive.asp#1062520986072822474|archive-date        = 2006-12-30}}</ref>
