==影响与评价==
{{details|{{Tsl|en|List of awards and nominations received by William Gibson|威廉·吉布森提名和获奖作品列表}}}}
吉布森的行文为诸多学者所研究。2011年，一本研究吉布森行文的专著《{{Tsl|en|William Gibson: A Literary Companion|威廉·吉布森文学导读}}》出版。<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Frelik|first=Paweł|date=2012|title=Review of William Gibson: A Literary Companion|journal=Journal of the Fantastic in the Arts|volume=23|issue=3 (86)|pages=506–508|issn=0897-0521|jstor=24353095}}</ref>吉布森以影响力之巨，在1999年，被《卫报》记者{{Tsl|en|Stephen Poole|史蒂芬·普尔}}称为“近二十年最重要的小说家”。<ref name="nearing">{{cite news |first=Steven |last=Poole |title=Nearing the nodal |url=http://books.guardian.co.uk/reviews/sciencefiction/0,6121,98588,00.html |work=Books by genre |publisher=The Guardian |date=1999-10-30 |access-date=2007-11-03 |location=London |archive-date=2008-01-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080108060537/http://books.guardian.co.uk/reviews/sciencefiction/0,6121,98588,00.html |url-status=no }}</ref>吉布森首部获得业界认可的作品，是其长篇小说处女作《[[神经漫游者|神经漫游者]]》，史无前例地获得了三大科幻小说奖（即[[星云奖|星云奖]]、[[菲利普·K·迪克纪念奖|菲利普·K·迪克纪念奖]]、[[雨果奖|雨果奖]]），《{{Tsl|en|Mail & Guardian|邮政卫报}}》就此形容道：“这就像是同一年获得了科幻小说界的[[龚古尔奖|龚古尔]]、[[布克奖|布克]]、[[普利策奖|普利策]]一样。”<ref name="mail&guardian"/>在科幻圈子外，《神经漫游者》作为“对1980年代末时的生活的一种唤起”所得到的业界和大众关注，同样也是史无前例的。<ref name="fitting">{{cite book |last = Fitting |first = Peter |editor = Penley, C. |editor2=Ross, A. |title = Technoculture |publisher = [[University_of_Minnesota_Press|University of Minnesota Press]]
| location = [[Minneapolis|Minneapolis]] |isbn =978-0-8166-1930-6 |oclc =22859126 |pages = [https://archive.org/details/technoculture00penl/page/295 295–315] |chapter = The Lessons of Cyberpunk |quote = [Gibson's work] has attracted an audience from outside, people who read it as a poetic evocation of life in the late eighties rather than as science fiction. |date=July 1991|title-link = Technoculture }}</ref>而《[[观察家报|观察家报]]》注意到，“《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》过了十年”才开始提及这部小说。<ref name="observer"/>吉布森的作品引起了世界各地的关注，受众不限于科幻爱好者。据劳拉·米勒所言，这是因为“读者发现，在（他）幻想的，时而径至于偏执的作品中折射出了对当代社会惊人的准确预言。”<ref name="miller">{{cite book | last = Miller | first = Laura | title = The Salon. Com Reader's Guide to Contemporary Authors | publisher = Penguin Books | location = New York | year = 2000 | isbn = 978-0-14-028088-3 | oclc = 43384794 | chapter = Introduction | chapter-url = http://archive.salon.com/books/feature/2000/08/11/guide_intro/index.html | url = https://archive.org/details/saloncomreadersg00mill }}</ref>这些作品经常被评论家带入[[后工业时代|后工业]]的语境中，据学者大卫·布兰德的说法，这种解读方式“构筑了一个对大型技术-社会关系的反映”，也是一种叙事化的后现代[[媒体文化|消费文化]]。<ref name="brande">{{cite journal | last = Brande | first = David | year = 1994 | title = The Business of Cyberpunk: Symbolic Economy and Ideology in William Gibson | journal = Configurations | volume = 2 | issue = 3 | pages = 509–536 | url = http://muse.jhu.edu/login?uri=/journals/configurations/v002/2.3brande.html | access-date = August 27, 2007 | doi = 10.1353/con.1994.0040 | archive-date = February 11, 2009 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090211053122/http://muse.jhu.edu/login?uri=%2Fjournals%2Fconfigurations%2Fv002%2F2.3brande.html | url-status = live }}</ref><ref name="sponsler">{{cite journal | last = Sponsler | first = Claire | date = Winter 1992 | title = Cyberpunk and the Dilemmas of Postmodern Narrative: The Example of William Gibson | journal = Contemporary Literature | volume = 33 | issue = 4 | pages = 625–644 | doi = 10.2307/1208645 | jstor = 1208645 | s2cid = 163362863 | url = https://semanticscholar.org/paper/b9bb98706dd2f81907a886b8c655d94ee8cac1a9 | access-date = 2020-01-18 | archive-date = 2021-04-19 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210419035429/https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Cyberpunk-and-the-Dilemmas-of-Postmodern-Narrative%3A-Sponsler/b9bb98706dd2f81907a886b8c655d94ee8cac1a9 | url-status = no }}</ref>评论家称赞其对{{Tsl|en|late capitalism|晚期资本主义}}的描绘，<ref name="brande"/>和“对客观性，人类意识和由于技术而开始变得有问题的行为的重述”。<ref name="sponsler"/>塔蒂亚妮·拉帕齐库（Tatiani Rapatzikou） 在 《{{Tsl|en|The Literary Encyclopedia|文学百科全书}}》中，将吉布森称为“北美洲最受好评的科幻作家之一”。<ref name="litencyc"/>
===文化影响===
{{Quote box|align=right|width=30%|威廉吉布森——让我们变酷了的那个人。|salign=right|source=赛博朋克作家{{Tsl|en|Richard K. Morgan
|理查德·K·摩根}}<ref name="morgan"/>}}
在《{{Tsl|en|The Literary Encyclopedia|文学百科全书}}》中，拉帕齐库称吉布森的早期作品“革新了”当时被普遍认为“不重要”的科幻文学，<ref name="litencyc"/>而他作品中的后现代美学促进了{{Tsl|en|Science fiction studies|科幻研究}}新角度的发展。<ref name="hollinger"/>电影制作人玛丽安·特伦希（Marianne Trench）称，吉布森描绘的幻景“在真实世界中激起了火花”，史无前例地“决定了人们如何思考和谈论”科幻文学。<ref name="mystic">Trench, Marianne and Peter von Brandenburg, producers. 1992. ''Cyberpunk. Mystic Fire Video'': Intercon Productions.</ref>1984年《神经漫游者》的出版迎合了文化潮流，<ref name="hollinger"/>{{Tsl|en|Larry McCaffery|拉里·麦卡菲里}}因此认为，吉布森实际上开启了[[赛博朋克|赛博朋克]]运动，<ref name="project cyberpunk interview"/>是“使整个运动看起来新颖、超凡的那一位新颖、超凡的作家。”<ref name="storming"/>{{efn|name=1962 Internet}}吉布森的作品，不仅是赛博朋克和[[蒸汽朋克|蒸汽朋克]]的核心作品，更被太空历史学家{{Tsl|en|Dwayne A. Day|德韦恩·A·戴}}誉为太空背景科幻小说（又名“太阳科幻”，"solar sci-fi"）最优秀的代表作，并称其为“可能是（太阳科幻小说中）唯一超越了单纯的幻想，而发人深省的作品”。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thespacereview.com/article/1108/1|title=Miles to go before the Moon|website=[[The_Space_Review|The Space Review]]|date=2008-04-21|access-date=2008-04-21|last=Day|first=Dwayne A.|author-link=Dwayne A. Day|archive-date=2008-05-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080514130444/http://www.thespacereview.com/article/1108/1|url-status=no}}</ref>
[[File:William_Gibson_and_Cory_Doctorow.jpg|thumb]]（右）等[[赛博朋克|赛博朋克]]<ref name="morgan">{{cite web |url=http://www.richardkmorgan.com/articles/recommended-reading-list/ |title=Recommended Reading List |access-date=2010-07-04 |last=Morgan |first=Richard |author-link=Richard Morgan (author) |url-status=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100411060446/http://www.richardkmorgan.com/articles/recommended-reading-list/ |archive-date=2010-04-11 }}</ref> 和{{Tsl|en|Cyberpunk_derivatives#Postcyberpunk|后赛博朋克}}作家。<ref name="doctorow">{{cite web |last= Dyer-Bennet |first= Cynthia |url= http://www.well.com/conf/inkwell.vue/topics/95/Cory-Doctorow-Talks-About-Nearly-page02.html#post43 |title= Cory Doctorow Talks About Nearly Everything |access-date= 2007-08-30 |website= Inkwell: Authors and Artists |publisher= [[WELL_(virtual_community)|The Well]] |archive-date= 2007-09-27 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20070927195836/http://www.well.com/conf/inkwell.vue/topics/95/Cory-Doctorow-Talks-About-Nearly-page02.html#post43 |url-status= no }}</ref>吉布森在写作《{{Tsl|en|Spook Country|幽灵山村}}》时，也曾向多克托罗请教过技术方面的问题<ref name="amazon3">{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/blog/post/PLNK2T9UDN3CBLZNP |title=Writing Fiction in the Age of Google: William Gibson Q&A, Part 3 |access-date=2007-11-04 |date=2007-06-24 |website=Amazon Bookstore's Blog |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071120142029/http://www.amazon.com/gp/blog/post/PLNK2T9UDN3CBLZNP |archive-date=2007-11-20 |dead-url=no }}</ref>]]
据《观察家报》称，吉布森的早期小说“被新生的一代{{Tsl|en|Slacker}}和[[黑客文化|黑客]]发现，用作了一种人生指南。”<ref name="observer"/>他的小说使“[[赛博空间|赛博空间]]”、“上网冲浪”、“{{Tsl|en|Intrusion Countermeasures Electronics|ICE (赛博朋克)|ICE}}”、“脑后插管”、“[[脑植入物|神经植入物]]”等词成为流行语，并推广了网络意识（net consciousness）、虚拟交互（virtual interaction）和“矩阵”（"the matrix"）等概念。<ref name="mcluhan">{{cite journal |last=Doherty |first=Michael E., Jr. |date=September 1995 |title=Marshall McLuhan Meets William Gibson in "Cyberspace" |journal=CMC Magazine |url=http://www.ibiblio.org/cmc/mag/1995/sep/doherty.html |access-date=2007-10-28 |page=4 |archive-date=2007-10-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071020031637/http://www.ibiblio.org/cmc/mag/1995/sep/doherty.html |url-status=no }}</ref>吉布森在1982年出版的《整垮铬萝米》首创了“赛博空间”一词，{{efn|1=吉布森后来成功阻止了当时正计划向[[虚拟现实|虚拟现实]]领域扩展的[[Autodesk|Autodesk]]公司将“赛博空间”（cyberspace）一词注册成商标。<ref name="citizenship"/>}}<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Branch|first=Jordan|date=2020|title=What's in a Name? Metaphors and Cybersecurity|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/international-organization/article/whats-in-a-name-metaphors-and-cybersecurity/563998100A2FAF1E5DFDB5C52EC68569|journal=International Organization|volume=75|language=en|pages=39–70|doi=10.1017/S002081832000051X|s2cid=224886794|issn=0020-8183|access-date=2020-09-26|archive-date=2020-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927143522/https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/international-organization/article/whats-in-a-name-metaphors-and-cybersecurity/563998100A2FAF1E5DFDB5C52EC68569|url-status=no}}</ref>意指[[计算机网络|计算机网络]]构成的“大型自愿[[幻觉|幻觉]]”。<ref>{{cite book|last= Prucher|first= Jeff|title= Brave New Words: The Oxford Dictionary of Science Fiction|publisher= Oxford University Press|year= 2007|page= [https://archive.org/details/bravenewwordsoxf00pruc/page/31 31]|isbn= 978-0-19-530567-8|oclc= 76074298|url= https://archive.org/details/bravenewwordsoxf00pruc/page/31}}</ref>艺术家{{Tsl|en|Dike Blair|戴克·布莱尔}}评论道，吉布森“简练而生动的用词所展现的是围绕着技术的情绪，而不是（技术的）机制。”<ref name="liquid">"Liquid Science Fiction: Interview with William Gibson by Bernard Joisten and Ken Lum", ''Purple Prose'', (Paris), N°9, été, pp.10–16</ref>
吉布森的作品对一些流行音乐家也造成了影响：在音乐作品中受他小说影响的，有{{Tsl|en|Stuart Hamm|斯图尔特·哈姆}}{{efn|1=哈姆《{{Tsl|en|Kings of Sleep}}》 专辑中 《{{Tsl|en|Intrusion Countermeasures Electronics|ICE (赛博朋克)|Black Ice}}》、《{{Tsl|en|Count Zero|零伯爵}}》、《{{Tsl|en|The Winter Market|冬季市场|Kings of Sleep}}》 等音轨的名称，都出自吉布森的作品。<ref name="hamm">{{cite AV media notes |title=Kings of Sleep |title-link=Kings of Sleep |author=[[Stuart_Hamm|Stuart Hamm]] |year=1989 |type=CD liner |publisher=[[Relativity_Records|Relativity Records]] }}</ref>}}、[[比利·爱多尔|比利·爱多尔]]{{efn|1=1993年，爱多尔发行了一张名为《{{Tsl|en|Cyberpunk (album)|赛博朋克}}》的专辑，其中一道音轨题为《神经漫游者》。<ref name="citizenship"/> [[罗伯特·克里斯特高|罗伯特·克里斯特高]]对爱多尔对[[赛博朋克|赛博朋克]]的表达的评价很低，<ref name="christgau">{{cite news |url=http://www.robertchristgau.com/xg/rock/cyberpun-93.php |title=Virtual Hep |access-date=2007-11-11 |last=Christgau |first=Robert |author-link=Robert Christgau |date=1993-08-10 |newspaper=[[Village_Voice|Village Voice]] |archive-date=2012-07-31 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/69YnJ5YDi?url=http://www.robertchristgau.com/xg/rock/cyberpun-93.php |url-status=no }}</ref>而吉布森后来也说到，爱多尔“把（赛博朋克）搞得很蠢。”<ref name="salza"/>}}、{{Tsl|en|Warren Zevon|沃伦·泽文}}{{efn|1=泽文于1989年发行的专辑《{{Tsl|en|Transverse City}}》是受吉布森小说的启发而创作成的。<ref name="zevon">{{cite magazine |url=http://www.flakmag.com/opinion/zevon.html |title=Requiem for a Rock Satirist |access-date=November 11, 2007 |last=Cook |first=Bob |date=February 10, 2002 |magazine=[[Flak_Magazine|Flak Magazine]] |archive-date=2007-10-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071015202211/http://flakmag.com/opinion/zevon.html |url-status=no }}</ref>}}、{{Tsl|en|Deltron 3030}}<ref>{{cite web |url= https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/18499-deltron-3030-event-ii/ |title= Deltron 3030 Event II |last= Patrin |first= Nate |date= 2013-10-02 |website= Pitchfork |accessdate= 2021-06-26 |archive-date= 2021-06-30 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210630081918/https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/18499-deltron-3030-event-ii/ |dead-url= no }}</ref>、{{Tsl|en|Straylight Run}}（乐队名称即出自《神经漫游者》）<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/music/artist/straylight_run/artist.jhtml#bio |title=Straylight Run |access-date=2007-09-09 |website=MTV.com |url-status=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071001103652/http://www.mtv.com/music/artist/straylight_run/artist.jhtml#bio |archive-date=2007-10-01 }}</ref>、[[音速青春|音速青春]]<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.theguardian.com/music/2020/may/25/sonic-youth-where-to-start-in-their-back-catalogue |title= Sonic Youth: where to start in their back catalogue |last= Grayson |first= Haver Currin |date= 2020-05-25 |website= The Guardian |accessdate= 2021-06-26 |archive-date= 2021-06-28 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210628154657/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2020/may/25/sonic-youth-where-to-start-in-their-back-catalogue |dead-url= no }}</ref>等。

[[U2樂團|U2]]乐队的专辑《[[Zooropa|Zooropa]]》受《神经漫游者》的影响很深<ref name="citizenship">{{cite journal|title=William Gibson interview|first=J. Stephen|last=Bolhafner|journal=[[Starlog|Starlog]]|issue=200|date=March 1994|url=http://bolhafner.com/stevesreads/igib2.html|access-date=2009-07-14|page=72|archive-date=2011-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708082111/http://bolhafner.com/stevesreads/igib2.html|url-status=no}}</ref>，又为《神经漫游者》有声书版配乐，<ref name="citizenship"/>还在为吉布森作传的纪录片《威廉·吉布森的旅行》中出镜<ref name="nomaps"/>。吉布森也投桃报李，2009年八月作文点评其{{Tsl|en|Vertigo Tour|晕眩国度巡回演唱会}}，刊载于《[[连线|连线]]》杂志。<ref>{{cite journal | author = Gibson William | year = 2005 | title = U2's City of Blinding Lights | url = https://www.wired.com/wired/archive/13.08/u2.html | journal = [[Wired_(magazine)|Wired]] | volume = 13 | issue = 8 | access-date = 2017-03-12 | archive-date = 2012-10-24 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20121024081431/http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/13.08/u2.html | url-status = no }}</ref>{{Tsl|en|Zeromancer}}乐队也得名于《神经漫游者》。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mk-magazine.com/interviews/archives/000132.php|title=Interviews: Zeromancer|website=[[MK_Magazine|MK Magazine]]|date=2003-11-01|access-date=2008-09-02|archive-date=2008-07-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080704054932/http://www.mk-magazine.com/interviews/archives/000132.php|url-status=no}}</ref>

1999年上映的电影《[[黑客帝国|黑客帝国]]》从标题（"''The Matrix''"）到角色再到故事元素，均受《{{Tsl|en|Sprawl trilogy|蔓生三部曲}}》的启发。<ref>{{cite journal |last=Hepfer |first=Karl |year=2001 |title=The Matrix Problem I: The Matrix, Mind and Knowledge |journal=Erfurt Electronic Studies in English |url=http://webdoc.sub.gwdg.de/edoc/ia/eese/artic21/hepfer/3_2001.html |access-date=2007-08-27 |issn=1430-6905 |archive-date=2004-07-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040705155710/http://webdoc.sub.gwdg.de/edoc/ia/eese/artic21/hepfer/3_2001.html |url-status=no }}</ref>其中，角色[[尼歐|尼歐]]和{{Tsl|en|Trinity (The Matrix)|崔妮蒂}}分别类似《{{Tsl|en|Count Zero|零伯爵}}》中的波比·纽马克和《{{Tsl|en|Johnny Mnemonics|约翰尼的记忆}}》及《[[神经漫游者|神经漫游者]]》中的{{Tsl|en|Molly Millions|莫莉·米利安斯}}。<ref name="mtv">{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/bands/m/movie_house/gibson_loder_030808/index.jhtml |title=The Matrix Preloaded |access-date=2007-11-07 |website=MTV's Movie House |publisher=[[Mtv.com|Mtv.com]] |last=Loder |first=Kurt |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070913111428/http://www.mtv.com/bands/m/movie_house/gibson_loder_030808/index.jhtml |archive-date=2007-09-13 |url-status=yes }}</ref>而崔妮蒂和《零伯爵》的主角透纳学习开直升飞机时一样，直接把教程下载到脑中；此外，《神经漫游者》和《黑客帝国》的情节都涉及力图摆脱人类控制的[[人工智能|人工智能]]。<ref name="mtv"/>影评界还注意到，《黑客帝国》的[[电影摄影|摄影]]和基调也与《神经漫游者》十分相似。<ref name="blackford">{{cite journal |last=Blackford |first=Russell |date=July 2004 |title=Reading the Ruined Cities |journal=Science Fiction Studies |volume=31 |issue=93 |url=http://www.depauw.edu/sfs/review_essays/blackford93.htm |access-date=2007-12-02 |archive-date=2007-11-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071124085516/http://www.depauw.edu/sfs/review_essays/blackford93.htm |url-status=no }}</ref>吉布森本人最初在观影之后，对《黑客帝国》未予置评，<ref name="nomaps"/>而后来则称其为“‘赛博朋克’中的极品”。<ref name=SFinfluences>{{cite web|url=http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_01_01_archive.asp#90244012|title=The Matrix: Fair Cop|first=William|last=Gibson|date=2003-01-28|access-date=2007-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070926221513/http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_01_01_archive.asp#90244012|archive-date=2007-09-26|url-status=yes}}</ref>2008年，吉布森获颁发[[西门菲莎大学|西门菲莎大学]]和{{Tsl|en|Coastal Carolina University|卡罗来纳海岸大学}}的荣誉博士学位，<ref>{{cite news|url=http://readingeagle.com/article.aspx?id=91460|title='Cyberspace' coiner returns to native SC for honorary degree|agency=Associated Press|work=Reading Eagle|date=2008-05-10|access-date=2008-06-08|archive-date=2014-07-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714215441/http://www2.readingeagle.com/article.aspx?id=91460|url-status=yes}}</ref>同年被选入[[流行文化博物館|科幻奇幻名人堂]]，由与吉布森有合作的好友{{Tsl|en|Jack Womack|杰克·沃马克}}致辞。<ref name=sfhof2008>
{{cite web|url=http://www.empsfm.org/press/index.asp?articleID=1259 |title=2008 Science Fiction Hall of Fame Ceremony Tickets On Sale May 15 |access-date=2013-03-21 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080510121729/http://www.empsfm.org/press/index.asp?articleID=1259 |archive-date=2008-05-10}}. Press release April/May 2008. Experience Music Project and Science Fiction Museum and Hall of Fame (''empsfm.org''). Archived May 10, 2008. Retrieved 2013-03-19.</ref>

===预见，及预想造成的影响===
{{Quote box|align=right|width=30%|未来已经到来，只是分布不均。|salign=right|source=——威廉·吉布森<ref>{{cite news| title = Virtual Reality Check Digital Daydreams, Cyberspace Nightmares| work = San Francisco Examiner| date = 1992-04-19 | page = C1| first = Scott | last = Rosenberg}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last= btr |date= 2020-01 |title= 语言并不模仿现实，语言创造现实 |url= https://www.sohu.com/a/376845436_262582 |journal= 思南文学选刊 |access-date= 2021-07-11 |quote= 刊于《思南文学选刊》（2020年第一期）资讯栏目……（吉布森）最有名的警句是：‘未来已经到来，只是分布不均。’ |archive-date= 2021-09-21 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210921044457/https://www.sohu.com/a/376845436_262582 |dead-url= no }}</ref>}}
早在早期互联网在1980年代初出现之前，吉布森就已在《神经漫游者》中用“矩阵”（"[[wikt:matrix|matrix]]"）一词来形容互联网的形象。<ref>{{cite IETF |rfc=801 |last=Postel |first=J. |date=November 1981 |title=NCP/TCP Transition Plan}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Zakon, Robert H|title=Hobbes' Internet Timeline v8.2|url=http://www.zakon.org/robert/internet/timeline/|publisher=Zakon Group LLC|date=2006-11-01|access-date=2007-10-31|archive-date=2009-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090505235502/http://www.zakon.org/robert/internet/timeline/|url-status=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.netlingo.com/lookup.cfm?term=matrix |title=Matrix |access-date=2007-09-09 |website=Netlingo |archive-date=2007-09-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927175507/http://www.netlingo.com/lookup.cfm?term=matrix |url-status=no }}</ref>这意味着吉布森在[[万维网|万维网]]出现多年以前，就设想了一种环球[[电信网络|通讯网络]]；<ref name="spike">{{cite journal| last = Johnston| first = Antony| date = August 1999| title = William Gibson : All Tomorrow's Parties : Waiting For The Man| journal = [[Spike_Magazine|Spike Magazine]]| url = http://www.spikemagazine.com/0899williamgibson.php| access-date = 2007-10-14| archive-date = 2007-06-08| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070608133252/http://www.spikemagazine.com/0899williamgibson.php| url-status = no}}</ref>虽然，类似的观念此前就已有人提出，其中也包括一些科幻作家。{{efn|1={{Tsl|en|John Brunner|约翰·布鲁纳}}著于1975年的小说《{{Tsl|en|The Shockwave Rider|电波骑士}}》是互联网和其深远的社会效应以及[[赛博朋克|赛博朋克]]这一门类的先声。<ref name="FutureTrace">{{cite web |url=http://www.anu.edu.au/people/Roger.Clarke/DV/NotesAntiUtopia.html |title=A 'Future Trace' on Dataveillance: The Anti-Utopian and Cyberpunk Literary Genres |author=Roger Clarke |year=1993 |access-date=2008-09-17 |url-status=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080814085852/http://www.anu.edu.au/people/Roger.Clarke/DV/NotesAntiUtopia.html |archive-date=2008-08-14 }}</ref><ref name="Edging">{{cite book |title=Edging Into the Future |last=Hollinger |first=Veronica |author2=Joan Gordon |year=2002 |publisher=University of Pennsylvania Press |isbn=978-0-8122-1804-6 |page=35 }}</ref>}}{{efn|name=1962 Internet|1=一组遍布世界各地、互相连接的计算机，所有人都可以用来不分地点地访问数据、使用程序这一想法，最早见于1962年当时为[[國防高等研究計劃署|國防高等研究計劃署]]工作的[[约瑟夫·利克莱德|约瑟夫·利克莱德]]的一系列关于“银河系网络”（Galactic Network）的备忘录。<ref>{{Cite web |author=Barry M. Leiner |author2=[[Vinton_G._Cerf|Vinton G. Cerf]] |author3=[[David_D._Clark|David D. Clark]] |author4=[[Robert_E._Kahn|Robert E. Kahn]] |author5=[[Leonard_Kleinrock|Leonard Kleinrock]] |author6=Daniel C. Lynch |author7=[[Jon_Postel|Jon Postel]] |author8=[[Lawrence_Roberts_(scientist)|Larry G. Roberts]] |author9=Stephen Wolff |title=A Brief History of the Internet |version=3.32 |publisher=[[Internet_Society|Internet Society]] |page=1011 |date=2003-12-10 |url=http://www.isoc.org/internet/history/brief.shtml |access-date=2007-11-03 |arxiv=cs/9901011 |bibcode=1999cs........1011L |archive-date=2001-12-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20011222202333/http://www.isoc.org/internet/history/brief.shtml |url-status=no }}</ref>}}在创作《{{Tsl|en|Burning Chrome|整垮铬萝米}}》时，吉布森“产生了一种直觉，感觉（互联网）会改变一切，就像汽车普及造成的大改观一样。”<ref name="nomaps"/>1995年，吉布森提出，互联网的出现，演变和发展这一过程是“本世纪内人类成就中史无前例的一个，也是最有趣的一个”，作为一种新文明的出现，其重要性堪与城市的出现相类；<ref name="josefsson">{{cite interview |last=Gibson |first=William |interviewer=Dan Josefsson |title=I Don't Even Have A Modem |publisher=[[SVT2|TV2]] |location=Stockholm |date=November 3, 1994 |url=http://www.josefsson.net/gibson/ |work=[[Rapport_(news_programme)|Rapport]] |access-date=November 5, 2007 |archive-date=2007-10-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071011022230/http://josefsson.net/gibson/ |url-status=no }}</ref>2000年，又预测互联网会导致[[民族国家|民族国家]]的消亡。<ref name="nomaps"/>
[[File:Scylla-_a_book_of_the_dead.jpg|thumb]]多有预见，并以此对其造成影响，使社会提前适应之，以此闻名。2008年3月14日摄于法国巴黎斯库拉（Scylla）书店]]
观察家注意到，吉布森对网络发展造成的影响，已不止于预测；他被公认为远在主流社会认识互联网之前，就“建立了[[信息时代|互联网时代]]的图像志”。<ref name="riding shotgun">{{cite news |last=Leonard |first=Andrew |date=February 2001 |title=Riding shotgun with William Gibson |work=[[Salon.com|Salon.com]] |url=http://archive.salon.com/tech/feature/2001/02/07/gibson_doc/index.html |access-date=2007-11-06 |url-status=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071007141619/http://archive.salon.com/tech/feature/2001/02/07/gibson_doc/index.html |archive-date=2007-10-07 }}</ref>吉布森在《[[神经漫游者|神经漫游者]]》中提出了“{{Tsl|en|meatpuppet|真人傀儡}}”这一概念；[[虚拟性交|虚拟性交]]这一现象，也被认为是他首创的：他本人并未参与这种行为，而是首创了其概念。<ref>{{cite news |first=Jayne M. |last=Blanchard |title=Sci-Fi Author Gibson Is 'Cyber'-Crowd's Guru |work=[[St._Paul_Pioneer_Press|St. Paul Pioneer Press]] |publisher=[[Digital_First_Media|MediaNews Group]] |date=1993-09-12 |quote= 威廉吉布森虽然想出了虚拟性交这个概念，他可从来没想跟这种事沾上一点边，我可得说明白了。我还得解释一下，这不是他死正经；这是因为科幻比现实精彩多了，科幻里的东西，现实中根本赶不上，很多事情都是这样。}}</ref>为[[桌面环境|桌面环境]]创作电子艺术设计的先驱艺术家，自认其设计受到了吉布森的启发；<ref name="desktop">{{cite journal |url=https://www.wired.com/gadgets/mac/news/2002/11/56318 |title=Early Desktop Pic Ahead of Time |access-date=2008-01-10 |last=Kahney |first=Leander |date=2002-11-14 |journal=[[Wired_(magazine)|Wired]] |archive-date=2008-12-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081227134425/http://www.wired.com/gadgets/mac/news/2002/11/56318 |url-status=no }}</ref>艺术方面，吉布森还获[[帕森斯设计学院|帕森斯设计学院]]颁发荣誉博士学位。<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.mediacastermagazine.com/issues/ISArticle.asp?id=82442&issue=04032008|archive-url = https://archive.is/20130128161229/http://www.mediacastermagazine.com/issues/ISArticle.asp?id=82442&issue=04032008|url-status = yes|archive-date = 2013-01-28|title = Sci-Fi Writer, High-Tech Marketer on Awards Jury|website = Mediacaster|access-date = 2008-04-21|date = 2008-04-03}}</ref>{{Tsl|en|Stephen Poole|史蒂芬·普尔}}称，吉布森的《蔓生三部曲》“为日后在现实中爆炸性发展的电子游戏和互联网这些虚拟环境奠定了观念上的基础”。<ref name="nearing"/>吉布森的合作者{{Tsl|en|Jack Womack|杰克·沃马克}}在《神经漫游者》2000年再版后记中提出，吉布森对赛博空间的设想有可能经由《神经漫游者》在1984年的初版推动了互联网（特别是万维网）未来的发展，就此设问道：“会不会有这样一种可能，把某个事物写下来，实际上就是促成了它？”<ref name="neuromancer20th">{{cite book | last = Gibson | first = William |author2=Jack Womack | title = Neuromancer | url = https://archive.org/details/neuromancer0000gibs_t6z2 | publisher = Ace Books | location = New York | year = 2004 | isbn = 978-0-441-01203-9 |oclc = 55745255 |page=[https://archive.org/details/neuromancer0000gibs_t6z2/page/269 269]}}</ref>

研究吉布森的学者塔蒂亚妮·格·拉帕齐库（Tatiani G. Rapatzikou）在《威廉·吉布森小说中的哥特主题》中就赛博空间主题的起源评论道：
{{quote|吉布森描绘的这种从终端综摄一切的意象中产生、体现于他笔下的赛博空间矩阵中的视觉效果，是受他看到几个十几岁的年轻人在[[电子游戏厅|游戏厅]]玩电子游戏的经历启发而得到的：玩家紧张的姿势，游戏对终端空间写实的投射——如同在屏幕后存在一个真实的空间一样——都显示出这种对{{Tsl|en|The Real|实相界}}的体现操控了实相界自身。<ref name="rapatzikou">{{cite book | last = Rapatzikou | first = Tatiani | title = Gothic Motifs in the Fiction of William Gibson | publisher = Rodopi | location = Amsterdam | year = 2004 | isbn = 978-90-420-1761-0 |oclc = 55807961}}</ref>}}
吉布森被认为是为数不多探索了信息时代对城市社会空间构造未来发展的潜在影响的几位观察家之一。<ref name="posturbanism">{{cite journal |last=Dear |first=Michael |author2=Steven Flusty |date=March 1998 |title=Postmodern Urbanism |journal=Annals of the Association of American Geographers |volume=88 |issue=1 |pages=50–72 |doi=10.1111/1467-8306.00084}}</ref>吉布森对此的预见招致了一些批评：如{{Tsl|en|Mark Pesce|马克·佩斯}}，尽管承认本人深受吉布森这些预见的影响，并认为“没有其他作家（如吉布森般）如此雄辩地在情感上影响了黑客社群”，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://web.mit.edu/comm-forum/papers/pesce.html |title=Magic Mirror: The Novel as a Software Development Platform |access-date=2007-12-02 |last=Pesce |first=Mark |website=MIT Communications Forum |publisher=[[Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology|Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] |archive-date=2008-06-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080611015758/http://web.mit.edu/comm-forum/papers/pesce.html |url-status=no }}</ref>却摒弃了它们，斥其为“对暴力和脱离肉体的青春期幻想”。<ref name="pesce">{{cite news |url=http://www.salon.com/1998/06/13/feature947640934/ |title=3-D epiphany |access-date=2007-11-06 |last=Pesce |first=Mark |author-link=Mark Pesce |date=1998-07-13 |work=[[Salon.com|Salon.com]] |archive-date=2014-07-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714182045/http://www.salon.com/1998/06/13/feature947640934/ |url-status=no }}</ref>

小说《[[模式识别_(小说)|模式识别]]》的剧情，围绕着一系列匿名发布、散布于互联网各处的电影片段展开。书中人物在各个网站上，对制片者的身份、动机、制影手法、灵感来源进行推测，这与日后2006年{{Tsl|en|lonelygirl15}}这一系列影片引起的互联网现象暗合；吉布森本人后来否认自己的作品对lonelygirl15产生过影响。<ref>edition of August 14, 2006 of the free daily ''[[Metro_International|Metro International]]'', interview by Amy Benfer (amybenfer (at) metro.us)</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://adage.com/article/ad-and-marketing-book-reviews/lonelygirl15-william-gibson/122540 |title= Before Lonelygirl15, There Was William Gibson |last= Arndorfer |first= James B. |date= 2007-12-11 |website= Ad Age |accessdate= 2021-08-17 |archive-date= 2021-08-17 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210817115317/https://adage.com/article/ad-and-marketing-book-reviews/lonelygirl15-william-gibson/122540 |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/business/2006/09/17/the-lessons-of-lonelygirl-we-can-be-fooled-and-we-probably-dont-care/b406fcc1-a9a6-4ee5-a99e-9176ba9c26df/ |title= The Lessons of 'Lonelygirl': We Can Be Fooled, And We Probably Don't Care |last= Ahrens |first= Frank |date= 2006-09-17 |website= [[Washington_Post|Washington Post]] |accessdate= 2021-08-17 |archive-date= 2021-09-21 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210921044512/https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/business/2006/09/17/the-lessons-of-lonelygirl-we-can-be-fooled-and-we-probably-dont-care/b406fcc1-a9a6-4ee5-a99e-9176ba9c26df/ |dead-url= no }}</ref>吉布森对后来大行其道的[[真人秀|真人秀]]电视节目这一社会现象也作了正确的预测<ref name="crier">{{cite journal |last=Parker |first=T. Virgil |date=Summer 2007 |title=William Gibson: Sci-Fi Icon Becomes Prophet of the Present |journal=College Crier |volume=6 |issue=2 |url=http://www.collegecrier.com/interviews/int-0040.asp |access-date=2007-10-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071009042217/http://www.collegecrier.com/interviews/int-0040.asp |archive-date=2007-10-09 |url-status=yes }}</ref>：如《{{Tsl|en|Virtual Light|虚拟之光}}》中就描写了一个以《{{Tsl|en|Cops (TV program)|美国警察 (电视节目)|美国警察}}》为戏仿原型而加以夸张的真人秀节目。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_09_01_archive.asp#106252098607282247 |title=Humility and Prescience |access-date=2007-11-26 |last=Gibson |first=William |date=2003-09-03 |work= |url-status=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061230140902/http://www.williamgibsonbooks.com/blog/2003_09_01_archive.asp#106252098607282247 |archive-date=2006-12-30 }}</ref>

{{Quote box|align=right|width=35%|有预见性的作家这个说法我能接受。先知谈不上。有这么一个事，是在我1991年刚见到布鲁斯·斯特林那会儿，我当时就喜欢上他了。（原文如此） 我们先握了个手，然后他就说，“干咱们这行简直了！咱们就四处忽悠人去，然后咱们还能挣着钱。咱们把这破玩意儿编出来，还他妈真有人信。”|salign=right|source=——2008年3月，吉布森在''ActuSf''上的采访<ref name=actusf>{{cite interview |last=Gibson |first=William |interviewer=Eric Holstein and Raoul Abdaloff |title=Interview de William Gibson VO |url=http://www.actusf.com/spip/article-5710.html |type=transcription |work=ActuSF |location=Paris |date=March 2008 |access-date=April 6, 2008 |archive-date=2008-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080405080902/http://www.actusf.com/spip/article-5710.html |url-status=no }}</ref>}}

在1988年的一次采访中，吉布森被问到他作品中的[[BBS|BBS]]术语是否与他使用BBS的经验有关时，提到自己“在写《神经漫游者》的时候就没怎么碰过[[个人电脑|电脑]]”，而与有大量BBS使用者的科幻社群的成员比较熟悉；在作品中经常出现的电脑游戏，吉布森同样也没玩过。<ref name="gibson198809">{{cite news | title=An Interview with William Gibson | url=http://www.cgwmuseum.org/galleries/index.php?year=1988&pub=2&id=51 | work=Computer Gaming World | date=September 1988 | access-date=November 3, 2013 | page=30 | archive-date=2019-10-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191002203041/http://www.cgwmuseum.org/galleries/index.php?year=1988&pub=2&id=51 | url-status=no }}</ref>吉布森写作《神经漫游者》，用的是一台1927年产的橄榄绿色爱马仕便携[[打字机|打字机]]，自述道：“就像是当年[[海明威|海明威]]出门的时候用的”。<ref name="mail&guardian"/>{{r|gibson198809}}{{r|gibson198809}}{{efn|1=1992年7月16日，吉布森在《重启蒙娜丽莎》中的《作者后记》中写道：
<blockquote>我写《神经漫游者》时，用的是一台所谓“发条打字机”，就是朱利·迪恩在千叶城的办公室里的那种，你可能留意过的。那是一台爱马仕2000手动便携式打字机，是1930年代产的。它很耐用，又非常典雅，是E. PAILLARD & Cie S.A. YVERDON (SUISSE)这座工厂的产物。上覆有盖，比我现在用来写作的{{Tsl|en|Macintosh SE/30}}稍轻，表面刷了一层奇特的绿黑相间的裂纹漆，大概是要让人想起会计用的账簿封皮的颜色。按键也是绿色的，赛璐珞制，上面字母和符号的字样则是金丝雀黄色的。（我有一次不小心把Shift键用点着的烟头蹭了一下，于是这种早期塑料就给我来了一个现身说法，充分证明了自己有多么易燃。）想当年，爱马仕2000打字机是全世界便携打字机里面数一数二的，价格也最昂贵。我手头的这台是我妻子继祖父的，他当初算是个记者，当时就用它来写文章，赞美[[罗伯特·彭斯|罗伯特·彭斯]]的诗歌。我第一次用这台打字机，是上本科时用来写英语文学论文，之后我头几次试着写短篇小说，再然后到《神经漫游者》，都是用它写的；电脑是从来就没怎么真的用过。</blockquote>}}
1988年，吉布森改用[[Apple_IIc|Apple IIc]]电脑写作，软件上使用的则是{{Tsl|en|AppleWorks}}；电脑附有调制解调器（吉布森自称“就没用过”）。然而，截至1996年接受采访时，吉布森出于担心与陌生人通信会使自己分心、无法专注写作，并没有注册电子邮箱。<ref name="josefsson"/>而吉布森第一次访问互联网网页，则是在写作《{{Tsl|en|Idoru|伊朵儿}}》时，请网页开发者为他设立个人站点之后了：在看到网页之前，他本以为网页“应该跟我以前见过的电邮和讨论组这些东西差不多，更多地是纯文本；结果等我一看，当场就目瞪口呆了。”<ref name="salon interview">{{cite web |url=http://www.salon.com/weekly/gibson961014.html |title=William Gibson Webmaster |access-date=November 6, 2007 |last=Rosenberg |first=Scott |website=The Salon Interview |publisher=[[Salon.com|Salon.com]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070907144823/http://www.salon.com/weekly/gibson961014.html <!--Added by H3llBot--> |archive-date=September 7, 2007 }}</ref>2007年，在被问及用哪款电脑写作、有何电脑配件时，吉布森这样说道：“我就只有一台2005年产的[[PowerBook_G4|PowerBook G4]]，1[[吉字节|G]]内存，（还有一个）[[无线路由器|无线路由器]]，就这几样。我就是赶不上时髦，基本上是赶不上。实话实说，我对电脑本身从来兴趣就不大。我观察的不是电脑，我观察的是围着电脑转的人，看他们都干些什么。现在做这种观察越来越困难了，因为一切都是在‘围着电脑转’。”<ref name="spook-country"/>

